{"title_page": "Wangpo Tethong", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Wangpo Tethong\n| image              = Wangpo Tethong.jpg\n| caption            = Tethong in 2013\n| birthname          = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1963|4|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Trogen]], Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden, Switzerland\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| nationality        = Swiss\n| other_names        = \n| education          = [[University of Z\u00fcrich]]\n| occupation         = communications consultant, historian, spokesperson, writer, politician\n| notable works      = \n| style              = \n| yearsactive        = since 1988\n| known_for          = Member of the 15th [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]]\n| awards             = \n| website            = \n}}\n'''Wangpo Tethong''' (born 16 April 1963, [[Trogen]],<ref name=\"vtje\">{{cite web|url=http://vtje.org/de/elections/wangpo-tethong/|title=Verein Tibeter Jugend in Europa: Wangpo Tethong|publisher=vtje.org|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-12-01}}</ref> [[Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]) He is the owner and managing director of Tethong Kommunikation. He is a former party secretary of the Green Party Canton of Zurich, spokesperson of Greenpeace Switzerland and worked as a senior consultant for a Swiss consultancy company. He is also known as a Swiss\u2013[[Tibetan people|Tibetan]] activist, writer and member of the 15th [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]].\n\n== Life and work ==\nWangpo Tethong was born to Tibetan refugees at the [[Kinderdorf Pestalozzi]] in [[Trogen]], [[Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]. He studied history and law at the [[University of Z\u00fcrich]],<ref name=\"exileaschallenge\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=eR6qa-BQ8p0C&pg=PA482&hl=de#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Exile as Challenge: The Tibetan Diaspora, page 482|publisher=Hyderabad Orient Longman|author1=Dagmar Bernstorff  |author2=Hubertus von Welck |lastauthoramp=yes |language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref> where he graduated with the master's degree (phil. I) from the philosophial departement in 1997.<ref name=\"rangzen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rangzen.net/author/wangpo/|title=Articles by Wangpo Tethong|publisher=rangzen.net|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988 Tethong assisted the German [[Green Party of Switzerland|''Die Gr\u00fcnen'']] politicians [[Petra Kelly]] and [[Gert Bastian]], convenors of the first international hearing on Tibet.<ref name=\"tricycle\">{{cite web|url=http://tricycle.org/magazine/anguish-tibet/|title=The Anguish of Tibet|publisher=tricycle.org|author=Christine Keyser, edited by [[Petra K. Kelly]], [[Gert Bastian]], and Pat Aiello|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref> From 1988 to 1989 Tethong was a board member of the [[Tibetan Youth Congress]] (TYC),<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> and between 1986 and 1990 president of the ''Tibetan Youth Association Europe'' and board member of the ''Verein Tibeter Jugend in Europa'' (literally: ''Association of Tibetan Youth in Europe'').<ref name=\"vtje\"/><ref name=\"exileaschallenge\"/> He co-founded the ''Studentische Arbeitsgemeinschaft f\u00fcr Tibet'' (STAFT) at the University of Z\u00fcrich in 1989, and was co-editor of the Tibetan-German magazine ''Bod Shon'' (''Junges Tibet'', literally \"Young Tibet\") from 1989 to 1995. Since 2001 he is the elected president of the ''Gesellschaft Schweizerisch-Tibetische Freundschaft'' (GSTF), literally ''Swiss-Tibetan Friendship Society''. Wangpo also served as party secretary and spokesperson of the [[Green Party of Switzerland|Green Party]] in the [[Canton of Z\u00fcrich]] from 1997 to 1999.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> Tethong was also a co-initiator of the [[Tibetan Freedom Radio]] that broadcasts a Tibetan and Chinese radio service, co-founder of ''Lamt\u00f6n'', an advice center for Tibetan refugees in Switzerland in 2004, chairmen of the ITSN Olympics Working Group from 2001 to 2008 and since 2008 president of the National Olympic Committee of Tibet. He also initiated ''ICT Deutschland'' in 2004, in 2008 ''Filming for Tibet'' and one year later ''Tibet Film Festival''.<ref name=\"vtje\"/>\n[[File:Die Schweiz f\u00fcr Tibet - Tibet f\u00fcr die Welt - GSTF Solidarit\u00e4tskundgebung am 10 April 2010 in Z\u00fcrich IMG 5703.JPG|thumb|Solidarity event at [[M\u00fcnsterhof]] in Z\u00fcrich on occasion of a visit by HH [[14th Dalai Lama]] in April 2010|262x262px]]\nAs the first exile Tibetan, he carried out a daring protest at the ''Tiananmen Square'' in Beijing in 2006. Among other events, Tethong also organized the manifestations with HH [[14th Dalai Lama]] in Berlin (Germany), Wien (Austria) and Z\u00fcrich (Switzerland).<ref name=\"vtje\"/> Since April 2000 Tethong is the mediaofficer of [[Greenpeace Switzerland]], since 2006 senior consultant for the Z\u00fcrich-based ''Kampagnenforum'',<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> an agency for development and implementation of participatory communication campaigns. He works as freelancer, consultant for public affairs, and on communication and film production.<ref name=\"tibetswiss\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tibetswiss.ch/exileparlament-europe/articles/wangpo-tethong-558.html|title=Tibetan Community in Switzerland & Liechtenstein: Wangpo Tethong|publisher=tibetswiss.ch|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-12-01}}</ref><ref name=\"10vor10-20170830\">{{cite web|url=http://www.srf.ch/sendungen/10vor10/doppelbuerger-tibeter-in-der-schweiz-buerokratie-in-frankreich|title=Tibeter in der Schweiz|publisher=[[10vor10]]|author=|language=German|date=2017-08-30|accessdate=2017-08-31}}</ref>\n\n== Tibetan Parliament in Exile ==\nOn 6 May 2014 Wangpo Tethong was elected as member of the [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]] from Europe constituency, where he took the oath of office from speaker [[Penpa Tsering]] at a ceremony held at the Tibetan Parliament in [[Dharamshala]]. He replaced [[Chungdak Koren]] who submitted her resignation citing health reasons. Wangpo gained the third highest votes in the last parliamentary elections from Europe constituency, which is represented in the Tibetan Parliament by two members: he ''has been involved in various services to the Tibetan community including the campaign for jailed Tibetan filmmaker [[Dhondup Wangchen]]''. The 44 members of the 15th Tibetan Parliament arepresentent the three traditional provinces, four Tibetan Buddhist sects and the traditional [[B\u00f6n]] religion of Tibet. Its members are directly elected by Tibetan exiles above the age of 18 from their respective around the world.<ref name=\"phayul\">{{cite web|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=34858&article=Wangpo+Tethong+sworn+in+as+Tibetan+MP+from+Europe|title=Wangpo Tethong sworn in as Tibetan MP from Europe|publisher=phayul.com|author=Phuntsok Yangchen|language=|date=6 May 2014|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref><ref name=\"10vor10-20170830\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nWangpo Tethong is married, father of two children, and lives in [[Jona]], Canton of St. Gallen.<ref name=\"vtje\"/><ref name=\"tibetanpoliticalreview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tibetanpoliticalreview.org/project-updates/europeanchituecandidates|title=European Chitue Candidates|publisher=tibetanpoliticalreview.org|author=Phuntsok Yangchen|language=|date=24 November 2010|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref>\n\n== Publications (selected works) ==\n* 1995: University of Z\u00fcrich, 1995\u20131996 thesis in history.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/>\n* 1997: [[Universit\u00e4t Z\u00fcrich]], with Prof. Dr. J\u00f6rg Fisch, 1985\u20141997 study in General History, Constitutional Law, Economic and Social History.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/>\n* 2000: ''Der Wandel in der politischen Elite der Tibeter im Exil: Integrations- & Desintegrationsprozesse in der politischen Elite, 1950 bis 1979''. [[Tibet Institute Rikon]], {{ISBN|978-3-72060-036-1}}.\n* 2003: ''Between Cultures: Young Tibetans in Europe''. Translated by Susanne Martin, in ''Exile as Challenge: The Tibetan Diaspora'' by Dagmar Bernstorff and  Hubertus von Welck. Hyderabad Orient Longman, Delhi, ISBN.\n* 2006: with Alexander Hauri: ''\u00dcberschwemmungen in der Schweiz. Klimawandel und seine Auswirkungen''. Greenpeace Schweiz, Bern 2006.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Wangpo Tethong}}\n* [https://tethong.ch Tethong Kommunikation]\n* [https://chitueblog.wordpress.com/ Wangpo Tethong's ''My Chitue Blog'' on wordpress]\n\n{{Portal bar|China|Asia}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tethong, Wanpgo}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:University of Zurich alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]\n[[Category:People from Rapperswil-Jona]]\n[[Category:Swiss male writers]]\n[[Category:Tibetan politicians]]\n[[Category:Swiss people of Tibetan descent]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of the Central Tibetan Administration]]\n[[Category:Tibetan Buddhists from Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Tibetan people]]\n[[Category:Political writers]]\n[[Category:Swiss activists]]\n[[Category:Swiss bloggers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swiss politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swiss poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swiss writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swiss writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n[[Category:Male bloggers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Wangpo Tethong\n| image              = Wangpo Tethong.jpg\n| caption            = Tethong in 2013\n| birthname          = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1963|4|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Trogen]], Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden, Switzerland\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| nationality        = Swiss\n| other_names        = \n| education          = [[University of Z\u00fcrich]]\n| occupation         = communications consultant, historican, spokesperson, writer, politician\n| notable works      = \n| style              = \n| yearsactive        = since 1988\n| known_for          = Member of the 15th [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]]\n| awards             = \n| website            = \n}}\n'''Wangpo Tethong''' (born 16 April 1963, [[Trogen]],<ref name=\"vtje\">{{cite web|url=http://vtje.org/de/elections/wangpo-tethong/|title=Verein Tibeter Jugend in Europa: Wangpo Tethong|publisher=vtje.org|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-12-01}}</ref> [[Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]) He is the owner and managing director of Tethong Kommunikation. He is a former party secretary of the Green Party Canton of Zurich, spokesperson of Greenpeace Switzerland and worked as a senior consultant for a Swiss consultancy company. He is also known as a Swiss\u2013[[Tibetan people|Tibetan]] activist, writer and member of the 15th [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]].\n\n== Life and work ==\nWangpo Tethong was born to Tibetan refugees at the [[Kinderdorf Pestalozzi]] in [[Trogen]], [[Canton of Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]. He studied history and law at the [[University of Z\u00fcrich]],<ref name=\"exileaschallenge\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=eR6qa-BQ8p0C&pg=PA482&hl=de#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Exile as Challenge: The Tibetan Diaspora, page 482|publisher=Hyderabad Orient Longman|author1=Dagmar Bernstorff  |author2=Hubertus von Welck |lastauthoramp=yes |language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref> where he graduated with the master's degree (phil. I) from the philosophial departement in 1997.<ref name=\"rangzen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rangzen.net/author/wangpo/|title=Articles by Wangpo Tethong|publisher=rangzen.net|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988 Tethong assisted the German [[Green Party of Switzerland|''Die Gr\u00fcnen'']] politicians [[Petra Kelly]] and [[Gert Bastian]], convenors of the first international hearing on Tibet.<ref name=\"tricycle\">{{cite web|url=http://tricycle.org/magazine/anguish-tibet/|title=The Anguish of Tibet|publisher=tricycle.org|author=Christine Keyser, edited by [[Petra K. Kelly]], [[Gert Bastian]], and Pat Aiello|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref> From 1988 to 1989 Tethong was a board member of the [[Tibetan Youth Congress]] (TYC),<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> and between 1986 and 1990 president of the ''Tibetan Youth Association Europe'' and board member of the ''Verein Tibeter Jugend in Europa'' (literally: ''Association of Tibetan Youth in Europe'').<ref name=\"vtje\"/><ref name=\"exileaschallenge\"/> He co-founded the ''Studentische Arbeitsgemeinschaft f\u00fcr Tibet'' (STAFT) at the University of Z\u00fcrich in 1989, and was co-editor of the Tibetan-German magazine ''Bod Shon'' (''Junges Tibet'', literally \"Young Tibet\") from 1989 to 1995. Since 2001 he is the elected president of the ''Gesellschaft Schweizerisch-Tibetische Freundschaft'' (GSTF), literally ''Swiss-Tibetan Friendship Society''. Wangpo also served as party secretary and spokesperson of the [[Green Party of Switzerland|Green Party]] in the [[Canton of Z\u00fcrich]] from 1997 to 1999.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> Tethong was also a co-initiator of the [[Tibetan Freedom Radio]] that broadcasts a Tibetan and Chinese radio service, co-founder of ''Lamt\u00f6n'', an advice center for Tibetan refugees in Switzerland in 2004, chairmen of the ITSN Olympics Working Group from 2001 to 2008 and since 2008 president of the National Olympic Committee of Tibet. He also initiated ''ICT Deutschland'' in 2004, in 2008 ''Filming for Tibet'' and one year later ''Tibet Film Festival''.<ref name=\"vtje\"/>\n[[File:Die Schweiz f\u00fcr Tibet - Tibet f\u00fcr die Welt - GSTF Solidarit\u00e4tskundgebung am 10 April 2010 in Z\u00fcrich IMG 5703.JPG|thumb|Solidarity event at [[M\u00fcnsterhof]] in Z\u00fcrich on occasion of a visit by HH [[14th Dalai Lama]] in April 2010|262x262px]]\nAs the first exile Tibetan, he carried out a daring protest at the ''Tiananmen Square'' in Beijing in 2006. Among other events, Tethong also organized the manifestations with HH [[14th Dalai Lama]] in Berlin (Germany), Wien (Austria) and Z\u00fcrich (Switzerland).<ref name=\"vtje\"/> Since April 2000 Tethong is the mediaofficer of [[Greenpeace Switzerland]], since 2006 senior consultant for the Z\u00fcrich-based ''Kampagnenforum'',<ref name=\"rangzen\"/> an agency for development and implementation of participatory communication campaigns. He works as freelancer, consultant for public affairs, and on communication and film production.<ref name=\"tibetswiss\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tibetswiss.ch/exileparlament-europe/articles/wangpo-tethong-558.html|title=Tibetan Community in Switzerland & Liechtenstein: Wangpo Tethong|publisher=tibetswiss.ch|language=|date=|accessdate=2015-12-01}}</ref><ref name=\"10vor10-20170830\">{{cite web|url=http://www.srf.ch/sendungen/10vor10/doppelbuerger-tibeter-in-der-schweiz-buerokratie-in-frankreich|title=Tibeter in der Schweiz|publisher=[[10vor10]]|author=|language=German|date=2017-08-30|accessdate=2017-08-31}}</ref>\n\n== Tibetan Parliament in Exile ==\nOn 6 May 2014 Wangpo Tethong was elected as member of the [[Tibetan Parliament in Exile]] from Europe constituency, where he took the oath of office from speaker [[Penpa Tsering]] at a ceremony held at the Tibetan Parliament in [[Dharamshala]]. He replaced [[Chungdak Koren]] who submitted her resignation citing health reasons. Wangpo gained the third highest votes in the last parliamentary elections from Europe constituency, which is represented in the Tibetan Parliament by two members: he ''has been involved in various services to the Tibetan community including the campaign for jailed Tibetan filmmaker [[Dhondup Wangchen]]''. The 44 members of the 15th Tibetan Parliament arepresentent the three traditional provinces, four Tibetan Buddhist sects and the traditional [[B\u00f6n]] religion of Tibet. Its members are directly elected by Tibetan exiles above the age of 18 from their respective around the world.<ref name=\"phayul\">{{cite web|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=34858&article=Wangpo+Tethong+sworn+in+as+Tibetan+MP+from+Europe|title=Wangpo Tethong sworn in as Tibetan MP from Europe|publisher=phayul.com|author=Phuntsok Yangchen|language=|date=6 May 2014|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref><ref name=\"10vor10-20170830\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nWangpo Tethong is married, father of two children, and lives in [[Jona]], Canton of St. Gallen.<ref name=\"vtje\"/><ref name=\"tibetanpoliticalreview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tibetanpoliticalreview.org/project-updates/europeanchituecandidates|title=European Chitue Candidates|publisher=tibetanpoliticalreview.org|author=Phuntsok Yangchen|language=|date=24 November 2010|accessdate=2015-11-30}}</ref>\n\n== Publications (selected works) ==\n* 1995: University of Z\u00fcrich, 1995\u20131996 thesis in history.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/>\n* 1997: [[Universit\u00e4t Z\u00fcrich]], with Prof. Dr. J\u00f6rg Fisch, 1985\u20141997 study in General History, Constitutional Law, Economic and Social History.<ref name=\"rangzen\"/>\n* 2000: ''Der Wandel in der politischen Elite der Tibeter im Exil: Integrations- & Desintegrationsprozesse in der politischen Elite, 1950 bis 1979''. [[Tibet Institute Rikon]], {{ISBN|978-3-72060-036-1}}.\n* 2003: ''Between Cultures: Young Tibetans in Europe''. Translated by Susanne Martin, in ''Exile as Challenge: The Tibetan Diaspora'' by Dagmar Bernstorff and  Hubertus von Welck. Hyderabad Orient Longman, Delhi, ISBN.\n* 2006: with Alexander Hauri: ''\u00dcberschwemmungen in der Schweiz. Klimawandel und seine Auswirkungen''. Greenpeace Schweiz, Bern 2006.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Wangpo Tethong}}\n* [https://tethong.ch Tethong Kommunikation]\n* [https://chitueblog.wordpress.com/ Wangpo Tethong's ''My Chitue Blog'' on wordpress]\n\n{{Portal bar|China|Asia}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tethong, Wanpgo}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:University of Zurich alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Appenzell Ausserrhoden]]\n[[Category:People from Rapperswil-Jona]]\n[[Category:Swiss male writers]]\n[[Category:Tibetan politicians]]\n[[Category:Swiss people of Tibetan descent]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of the Central Tibetan Administration]]\n[[Category:Tibetan Buddhists from Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Tibetan people]]\n[[Category:Political writers]]\n[[Category:Swiss activists]]\n[[Category:Swiss bloggers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swiss politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swiss poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Swiss writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Swiss writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n[[Category:Male bloggers]]\n", "name_user": "Will Sandberg", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wangpo_Tethong"}
{"title_page": "Anjali (actress)", "text_new": "{{about|the actress||Anjali (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anjali\n| image              = [[File:AnjaliWiki.jpg|200px|]]\n| caption            = Anjali at Indiaglitz photoshoot\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|06|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Razole, East Godavari district|Razole]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], India\n| residence          = \n| occupation         = Actress\n| alma mater         = \n | othername          = \n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n}}\n\n'''Anjali''' is an Indian film actress and model, who predominantly appears in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]]  and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films. Following a stint in modelling, she was cast in starring roles in two Telugu productions; her d\u00e9but film was the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film ''Photo'', which released in 2006, before bagging a role and gaining attention in the film ''[[Kattradhu Thamizh]]'' (2007) with [[Jiiva]]. In 2010 and 2011, she won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil]], for her performances in ''[[Angaadi Theru]]'' and ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]'' respectively, & [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards|Tamil Nadu State Film Award]] For [[Angadi Theru]] subsequently becoming recognised as one of the \"finest young actors\" in Tamil cinema,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anjali-eyeing-mass-films-news-tamil-lbyjrFcjfgb.html |title=Anjali eyeing mass films? |publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> and noted for mostly playing \"performance-oriented roles\"''.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-17/news-interviews/28370956_1_thoonga-nagaram-anjali-madurai |title=Anjali wants to do commercial cinema |publisher=The Times of India |date=17 January 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-anjali/20110915.htm |title=I want people to say there's no one like me |publisher=Rediff.com |date=15 September 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-08-20/news-interviews/28281372_1_image-makeover-anjali-film |title=Image makeover for Anjali |publisher=The Times of India |date=20 August 2010 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref>''\n \nHer Telugu re-entry occurred through ''Journey'' (Telugu dubbing of ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''), which garnered her critical acclaim.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/journey/movie-review/11145287.cms</ref> Followed by ''Journey'', she appeared in a string of successful films like ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]'', ''[[Balupu]]'', ''[[Masala (2013 film)|Masala]]'', ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]'' and ''[[Dictator (2016 film)|Dictator]]'', which made her one of the leading actresses in [[Telugu language|Telugu]]. She also received two [[Nandi Awards|Nandi awards]] for best actress for her performances in the films [[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]] and ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]''. In May 2016, she won great applause for her role in the Tamil Film ''[[Iraivi]]'', making huge impact on Tamil audiences. In August 2017, she appeared in an extended cameo role in director Ram's ''[[Taramani (film)|Taramani]]'' which earned good responses from both critics as well as audiences.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/aug/12/taramani-review-a-film- |title=Taramani }}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAnjali was born in [[Razole, East Godavari district|Razole]], [[East Godavari]] District, [[Andhra Pradesh]] on 16 June 1989. She has two brothers and a sister. She worked as a software engineer during her struggling days.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2010/04/09/stories/2010040950361600.htm |location=Chennai, India |work=The Hindu |title=My first break \u2013 Anjali |date=9 April 2010}}</ref> She completed her schooling in Razole <ref name=\"totaltollywood1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.totaltollywood.com/interviews/Anjali_2051.html |title=Anjali \u2013 Interviews in Telugu Movies |publisher=Totaltollywood.com |accessdate=21 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120105032829/http://www.totaltollywood.com/interviews/Anjali_2051.html |archivedate=5 January 2012}}</ref> and later moved to [[Chennai]] where she continued her studies, pursuing a degree in mathematics.<ref name=\"rediff1\">{{cite web |url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/apr/13/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-anjali-from-angadi-theru.htm |title=Meet the fiery Kani of Angadi Theru |publisher=Movies.rediff.com |date=13 April 2010 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> After completing her education, she began acting in short films, which paved the way for her entry into the film industry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ragalahari.com/functions/1759/photo-muhurat.aspx |title=Photo Muhurat Gallery \u2013 Telugu Cinema, Tollywood |publisher=Ragalahari.com |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> Anjali remarked that her parents had aspirations to become an actor and that they \"realised their dreams\" through her.<ref name=\"rediff1\"/>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2006\u20132008===\n\nIn 2002, Anjali was signed on to appear in director [[Kalanjiyam]]'s ''Sathamintri Muthamidu'' under the screen name of Sundhari, but the film later failed to materialise.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58928.html |title=Anjali signs handful - Tamil Movie News |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |date=2010-07-27 |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref><ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20030805141512/http://www.chennaionline.com/entertainment/filmplus/ntlaunch.asp</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/aug-06-04/25-08-06-nakul.html |title=Tamil movies : Will luck favor \u2018Boys\u2019 fame Nakul this time? |publisher=Webcache.googleusercontent.com |date=2013-09-02 |accessdate=2013-09-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918135527/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/aug-06-04/25-08-06-nakul.html |archivedate=18 September 2015 }}</ref> The director also began two other films with Anjali, ''Valiba Desam'' and ''En Kanavu Thaanadi'', though those also failed to materialise. During one of her modelling assignments, she was spotted by director [[Siva Nageswara Rao]], who offered her a starring role in his Telugu thriller film ''Photo'' (2006).<ref name=\"totaltollywood1\"/> Anjali portrayed a ghost haunting her murderers in ''Photo'', which co-starred two more newcomers, Anand and [[Muktha (actress)|Bhanu]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/review/8357.html |title=Photo Telugu Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=1 September 2006 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> She played the female lead in another Telugu venture, the romance film ''Premalekha Raasa'' (2007), directed by lyricist Kulasekhar, opposite a debutant again;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/preview/8721.html |title=Premalekha Raasa Telugu Movie Preview cinema review stills gallery trailer video clips showtimes |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=20 November 2006 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> both films garnered negative response,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/3170/telugu/photo/847/review.htm |title=Photo Review \u2013 Telugu Movie Review by Kishore |publisher=Nowrunning.com |date=6 September 2006 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> and performed poorly at the box office, failing to propel her career in Telugu cinema.\nanjali gets 18 crores as her salary for a film.\n\nShe made her Tamil film d\u00e9but later that year in ''[[Kattradhu Thamizh]]'', directed by [[Ram (director)|Ram]], which released to strong critical acclaim. Anjali won critical praise for her portrayal of Anandhi, the childhood friend and love interest of a young teacher-turned-psychopath (enacted by [[Jeeva (actor)|Jeeva]]). A ''Behindwoods'' critic wrote that she was \"a delight to watch and spellbinds the viewer with her beautiful fresh look and her performance\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-06/kattradhu-tamil-review.html |title=Cast crew Jeeva Anjali Karunas Direction Ram Music Yuvan Shankar Raja M R Film Productions |publisher=Behindwoods |date=26 November 2006 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> while Pavithra Srinivasan of ''[[Rediff]]'' described her as \"a breath of fresh air\" and \"the perfect foil to Jeeva's plethora of emotions\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/oct/05kt.htm |title=Katrathu Thamizh review |publisher=Rediff.com |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> Her performance earned her the [[Vijay Award for Best Debut Actress]] for that year,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |title='Happy Days' at the 55th Tiger Balm Filmfare South Awards |publisher=Bollyspice.com |accessdate=27 March 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090614085233/http://www.bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |archivedate=14 June 2009}}</ref> and she grew in popularity, leading her to several more offers, albeit the film proved commercially unsuccessful.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/45787.html |title=Anjali gets busy |publisher=indiagltz |accessdate=27 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326093314/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/45787.html |archivedate=26 March 2009 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musicindiaonline.com/ar/i/movie_name/9327/1/ |title='Happy Days' at the 55th Tiger Balm Filmfare South Awards |agency=\"Movie Review : Tamil M.A\" |publisher=musicindiaonline.com |accessdate=27 March 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090524062905/http://www.musicindiaonline.com/ar/i/movie_name/9327/1/ |archive-date=24 May 2009 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\nShe appeared in two films in 2008; ''[[Honganasu]]'', her first Kannada project and ''[[Aayudham Seivom]]'' in Tamil. The latter, which featured her as the female lead opposite [[Sundar C]], was panned by critics and she was criticised for accepting that role, with reviewers noting that she had nothing to do in the film,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/ayudham-seivom-review-tamil-14705298.html |title=Movie Review:Ayudham Seivom |publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/aayudham-movie-review.html |title=Aayudham Seivom \u2013 Movie review |publisher=behindwoods |accessdate=27 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090226053429/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/aayudham-movie-review.html |archivedate=26 February 2009 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/9772.html |title=Aayudham Seivom Tamil Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=30 June 2008 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> \"except roll her eyes\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2008/jun/27ssas.htm |title=Ayudham Seivom makes no impact |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=27 March 2009}}</ref>\n\n===2010\u20132012===\nShe next played Kani, a fiery, independent sales girl in a textile showroom in ''[[Angadi Theru]]'' (2010) which melted everyone's heart was released two years after her last venture. The [[Vasanthabalan]]-directed tragedy drama focussed on the lives of young employees who work in retail [[department stores]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/angadi-theru-review-tamil-14936554.html |title=Movie Review:Angadi Theru |publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Bhama Devi Ravi |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Angadi-Theru/movie-review/5731109.cms |title=Angadi Theru movie review: Wallpaper, Story, Trailer at Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=27 March 2010 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> The film was shot in real location at the [[Ranganathan Street]] in [[T Nagar]], Chennai with hidden cameras,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/angadi-theru-shot-with-hidden-cameras-news-tamil-kkfqJ0jhabi.html |title=Angadi Theru shot with hidden cameras! |publisher=Sify |date=24 March 2010 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> with Anjali disclosing that they wore the uniform of a particular textile company, passing off as real sales-people and selling goods.<ref name=\"rediff1\"/> ''Angadi Theru'' opened to rave reviews, whilst also fetching Anjali critical acclaim for her performance, who went on to win several accolades,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-28/news-interviews/29478904_1_role-actress-award-film |title=Anjali: Damsel in delight! |publisher=The Times of India |date=28 April 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-04/news-interviews/29735734_1_angadi-theru-anjali-film |title='An unforgettable evening' |publisher=The Times of India |date=4 July 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> She subsequently appeared in two family drama films; [[S Pictures]]' ''[[Rettaisuzhi]]'', in which she shared screen with veteran directors [[Bharathiraja]] and [[Kailasam Balachander|K Balachandar]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ayngaran.com/newsdetails.php?newsid=392 |title=Anjali about acting with veteran directors |publisher=[[Ayngaran]] |accessdate=27 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090311014907/http://www.ayngaran.com/newsdetails.php?newsid=392 |archivedate=11 March 2009 |url-status=live}}</ref> and ''[[Magizhchi]]'', co-starring and directed by Gowthaman. The latter released to favourable reviews,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2010/11/21/stories/2010112150020200.htm |location=Chennai, India |work=The Hindu |title=Bonding, bucolic style |date=21 November 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"indiaglitz.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/8740.html |title=Magizhchi Tamil Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=19 November 2010 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref> and Anjali received positive feedback on her performance, being labelled as \"impressive\",<ref name=\"indiaglitz.com\"/> and \"almost perfect as the young, a bit mischievous, village girl\";<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/magizhchi-movie-review.html |title=Magizhchi Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |date= |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref> however both films failed to succeed at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/star-track/20100916010941/Very-happy-to-be-part-of-Magizhchi---Anjali.col |title=Very happy to be part of 'Magizhchi' \u2013 Anjali &#124; startrack \u2013 Movies |publisher=ChennaiOnline |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, she first appeared in ''[[Payyans (film)|Payyans]]'' alongside [[Jayasurya]], which marked her d\u00e9but in [[Malayalam]] cinema,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anjali-is-jayasuryas-heroine-news-malayalam-kkfqnuahhaa.html |title=Anjali is Jayasurya's heroine |publisher=Sify |date=9 July 2010 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> followed by a lead female role in the [[Cloud Nine Movies]]-production ''[[Thoonga Nagaram]]'', in which she starred as an anchor in local television,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-thoonga-nagaram/20110207.htm |title=Review: Thoonga Nagaram has its moments |publisher=Rediff |date=7 February 2011 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref> and a [[cameo appearance]] in a song in ''[[Ko (film)|Ko]]'' that also featured other lead actors from [http://tamilcinema.co Tamil Cinema].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-01/news-interviews/28643250_1_special-appearances-kuselan-indian-films |work=The Times of India |title=It's cameo craze for Kollywood actors! |date=1 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tamilcinema.co |title=Tamil Cinema |last= |first= |date= |website=Tamil Cinema |access-date=}}</ref> She was then seen in the small-budget drama film ''[[Karungali]]'', directed by [[Kalanjiyam]]. [[Kalanjiyam]] had signed up Anjali, rechristening her as Sundari then, for a film titled ''Sathamindri Muthamidu'', even prior to ''Kattradhu Thamizh'', followed by three more films, all of which were cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58928.html |title=Anjali signs handful |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=27 July 2010 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref> Following her rise to fame post ''Angadi Theru'', Kalanjiyam revived one of the projects, namely ''Karungali'', with Anjali agreeing to part of it, owing to her prior commitments.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://reviews.in.88db.com/index.php/movie/movie-news/1482-anjali-an-actress-with-no-tanturms |title=Anjali an actress with no tanturms! |publisher=Reviews.in.88db.com |accessdate=8 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130327092314/http://reviews.in.88db.com/index.php/movie/movie-news/1482-anjali-an-actress-with-no-tanturms |archive-date=27 March 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The film featured her as a childless housewife living in an bad relationship with her husband,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jul-11-02/anjali-karungali-08-07-11.html |title=The Role Turned Down By Top Heroines |publisher=Behindwoods |date=8 July 2011 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/karungali-review-tamil-14975424.html |title=Movie Review:Karungali |publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref> and was a critical and commercial failure.\nWhile starring in ''Thoonga Nagaram'', she was offered a minor supporting role in another project of the production studio, ''[[Mankatha]]''.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\"/> The [[Ajith Kumar]]-starrer, directed by [[Venkat Prabhu]], was Anjali's first high-budget project and featured her as part of an [[ensemble cast]]. The film emerged a financial success and Anjali's highest-grossing film in her career, however her role in the film was small and not well received generally. Meanwhile, she was cast by director [[A R Murugadoss]] to perform a lead role in his maiden production ''[[Engeyum Eppodhum]]'' alongside [[Jai (actor)|Jai]], [[Sharvanand]] and [[Ananya (actress)|Ananya]], directed by his assistant [[M. Saravanan (film director)|M Saravanan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-04/news-interviews/28659087_1_film-anjali-role |title=Anjali to star in A R Murugadoss' next |publisher=The Times of India |date=4 March 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> Anjali essayed the role of a bold and dominating nurse,<ref>{{cite news |author=Subha J Rao |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2403041.ece |title=Arts / Cinema : Courting the camera |publisher=The Hindu |date=27 August 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011 |location=Chennai, India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110909113719/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2403041.ece |archive-date=9 September 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-09/news-interviews/30134307_1_anjali-characters-film |title=Engaeyum Eppodhum: A different equation! |publisher=The Times of India |date=9 September 2011 |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> with critics again heaping praise on her performance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/engeyum-eppodhum-review-tamil-14979311.html |title=Movie Review:Engeyum Eppodhum |publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> ''[[The Hindu]]'' wrote that she \"has given her best [and] steals the show in the climax\",<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/nxg/article2473051.ece |location=Chennai, India |work=The Hindu |first=Sai |last=Shyam G |title=Accidental success |date=21 September 2011 |access-date=25 September 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110925061506/http://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/nxg/article2473051.ece |archive-date=25 September 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> while ''[[Rediff.com|Rediff]]''{{'}}s Pavithra Srinivasan cited it was her \"who clearly walks away with the honours\", adding that \"the extent of her feelings emerges only at the end, and carries you away\" and calling it a \"noteworthy performance\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-engeyum-eppodhum/20110919.htm |title=Review: Go for Engeyum Eppodhum |publisher=Rediff.com |date= |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> She had her only starring role in 2012 in [[Sundar C]]'s ''[[Kalakalappu]]''. A critic from [[Deccan Chronicle]] wrote that \"Anjali scores well with her natural performance\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/movie-reviews/kalakalappu-review-served-lot-fun-099 |title=Kalakalappu review: Served with a lot of fun |publisher=Deccan Chronicle |date=13 May 2012 |accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014===\n\nIn 2013, she starred in the Telugu multi-starrer ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]'' along with [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]], [[Mahesh Babu]] and [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]]. The film went on to be a critical and commercial success, with many applauses for Anjali from the critics. Mahalakshmi Prabhakaran of DNA India commented that Anjali \"as the innocent Seetha...gives an easy breezy but endearing performance\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1788240/review-film-review-seethamma-vakitlo-sirimalle-chettu-telugu |title=Film review: Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu (Telugu) |publisher=DNA India |accessdate=12 January 2013<!--, 16:41 IST-->}}</ref> She later starred in [[A R Murugadoss]]' next production venture ''[[Vatthikuchi]]'' opposite Dhileban.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/85757.html |title=A R Murugadoss's 'Vathikuchi' |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=6 September 2012 |accessdate=6 September 2012}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews as did her performance. IndiaGlitz commented \"Anjali's character though is sugary; it's a reminiscent of so many of her characters in the past and leaves you with a sense of wanting variation\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/16480.html |title=Vathikuchi \u2013 An Ingenious matchstick that illuminates you |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=15 March 2013}}</ref> Her next release was ''[[Settai]]'', the Tamil remake of ''[[Delhi Belly (film)|Delhi Belly]]'', in which she starred opposite [[Arya (actor)|Arya]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-12-01/arya-santhanam-03-05-12.html |title=Arya and Santhanam's next to go on floor |work=Behindwoods |accessdate=3 May 2012}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews, though she was appreciated for her performance and looks. S Saraswati of Rediff commented \"Anjali, who is better known for deglamorised performances, has been given a brand new avatar for this film. Her clothes, hair and makeup have all been changed to suit her character\u2014that of a very confident and attractive Mumbai-based journalist\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-settai-not-patch-on-delhi-belly/20130405.htm |title=Review: Settai, not a patch on Delhi Belly |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=5 April 2013<!-- 13:35 IST-->}}</ref> After an [[item number]] in [[Suriya]]'s ''[[Singam II]]'', her first in her career,<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/anjali-to-do-item-number-in-singham-2-news-tamil-mlmklgedefesi.html</ref> she starred in two Telugu films, [[Gopichand Malineni]]'s ''[[Balupu]]'' opposite [[Ravi Teja]] and ''[[Masala (2013 film)|Masala]]'', the Telugu remake of ''[[Bol Bachchan]]'', opposite Venkatesh, for the second time in her career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/131016/entertainment-tollywood/article/anjali-hopes-svsc-magic-again |title=Anjali hopes for 'SVSC' magic again |work=Deccan Chronicle |access-date=14 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211141616/http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/131016/entertainment-tollywood/article/anjali-hopes-svsc-magic-again |archive-date=11 December 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2014, she appeared in a women-centric horror film titled ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]'' for the first time in her career.\n\n=== 2015\u2013present ===\nIn early 2015, Anjali returned to [[Kannada cinema|Sandalwood]] and starred opposite [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] in [[Rana Vikrama]] . Her d\u00e9but film in Kannada was [[Honganasu]] seven years ago. She broke the seven-year hiatus with that film. In Tamil, she appeared opposite [[Jayam Ravi]] alongside with [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]], [[Soori (actor)|Soori]] in [[Sakalakala Vallavan]]. In Telugu, she played a special cameo role of a lady don in [[Sankarabharanam (2015 film)|Sankarabharanam]], a Telugu film which has [[Nikhil Siddharth]] in lead. In 2016, her first release was in Telugu opposite Balayya Balakrishna titled [[Dictator (2016 film)|Dictator]] which declared Super-hit. Her role was well received by the audience. She signed a Tamil-Malayalam film ''[[Peranbu]]'' opposite [[Mammootty|Mammotty]] TV directed by Director Ram. A women-centric Tamil film speaking about violence against women directed by debutant director Sarvesh, assistant of [[Sasi (director)|Sasi]] which has Anjali in the lead. She plays the role of a beautician in this film. The first look of this film released and created a huge hype among the people. Kaanbathu Poi might be released in Telugu, too, if all things go well. In December 2017, her film with [[Jai (actor)|Jai]] & [[Janani Iyer]] titled ''[[Balloon]]'' directed by newcomer Sinish got good reviews and moderate-average performance at the box office.\n\n=== Women-centric films ===\nIn 2014, she appeared in a horror comedy women-centric film titled ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]'' which gained positive reviews all over and a box office hit with critics praising her performance. She received [[Nandi Award for Best Actress]], SICA Award For Best Telugu Actress 2015 and was nominated for many awards. Following ''Geethanjali'', she received many offers of women-centric films which she turned down all. Later in 2014, she signed a psycho action thriller Telugu film ''Chitrangada''. In early 2016, she signed a lady-oriented action thriller Tamil film ''Kanbathupoi'' directed by debutant Sarvesh opposite actor Amazath. Her films ''[[Mapla Singam]]'', ''[[Chitrangada: The Crowning Wish|Chitrangada]]'', ''[[Sarrainodu]]'', and ''[[Iraivi]]'' released.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/iraivi-film-about-women-who-bear-everything-and-put-anything-44493 |title=Iraivi }}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n; '''[[Filmfare Awards South]]'''\n* [[55th Filmfare Awards South|2007]]:[[55th Filmfare Awards South|Best Debut Actress]] - [[Kattradhu Thamizh]]\n* [[58th Filmfare Awards South|2011]]: [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil|Best Actress \u2013 Tamil]] \u2013 ''[[Angadi Theru]]''\n* [[59th Filmfare Awards South|2012]]: Best Actress \u2013 Tamil \u2013 ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''\n\n; '''[[Nandi Awards]]'''\n*[[Nandi Special Jury Award|Special Jury Award for Best Actress]] (2013) - ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]''\n* [[Nandi Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] (2014) \u2013 ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]''\n\n; '''[[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]]'''\n*[[Tamil Nadu State Film Award Special Prize]] - Best Actress for ''[[Angadi Theru]]''\n\n; [[South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n* [[1st South Indian International Movie Awards|2011]]: Best Actress \u2013 Tamil \u2013 ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''\n\n; [[Vijay Awards]]\n* [[2nd Vijay Awards|2008]]: [[Vijay Award for Best Debut Actress|Best Debut Actress]] \u2013 ''Kattradhu Thamizh''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starboxoffice.com/kollywood/vijayawards/about.html |title=Reliance Mobile Vijay Awards \u2013 The Awards Ceremony |publisher=[[Star Vijay]] |accessdate=27 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425145911/http://www.starboxoffice.com/kollywood/vijayawards/about.html |archivedate=25 April 2009 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[5th Vijay Awards|2011]]: [[Vijay Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] \u2013 ''Angadi Theru''\n* [[6th Vijay Awards|2012]]: Best Actress \u2013 ''Engeyum Eppodhum''\n\n; Other awards\n* 2011: [[Norway Tamil Film Festival Award for Best Actress]] \u2013 ''[[Angadi Theru]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madrasapattinam-wins-four-awards-news-tamil-le1jiQghjdg.html |title=Madrasapattinam wins four awards |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=28 April 2011 |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref>\n* 2011: Vikatan Award For Best Actress \u2013 ''[[Angadi Theru]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2011 [[Jaya TV|Film Fans Association Awards-Jaya TV]]  -''[[Angadi Theru]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2011: Tamil Cinema Press Award For Best Actress \u2013 ''[[Angadi Theru]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2012: Vikatan Award For Best Actress \u2013 ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2012: Chennai Times Film Award for Best Actor Female \u2013 ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2012 [[Jaya TV|Film Fans Association Awards-Jaya TV]]  -''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2012: V4 Entertainment Award for Best Actress \u2013 ''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-12-01/dhanush-anjali-03-01-12.html |title=Dhanush And Anjali \u2013 Best Actor And Actress |publisher=Behindwoods |date=3 January 2012 |accessdate=8 December 2012}}</ref>\n* 2012: [[Santosham Best Actress Award|Santosham Award For Best Actress in Tamil]]-''[[Engaeyum Eppothum]]''<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sScSndfcje0</ref>\n* 2013: Cine Maa Award for Best Performance{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2013: Big Telugu Entertainment Award for Best Actress - ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]''{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n* 2013: Nandi Special Jury Award for Best Actress - ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]''{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* 2015: SICA-South Indian Cinematographers Association AWARDS For Best Actress  ''[[Geethanjali (2014 film)|Geethanjali]]'' <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bbe \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb2\u0bbf (\u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0b95\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 4) |date=11 January 2015 |url=http://www.selliyal.com/?p=76861}}</ref>\n* 2018: [[Santosham Best Actress Award|Santosham Award For Best Actress in Tamil]]-''[[Iraivi]]''\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Language\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2006 || ''Photo'' || Swapna || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2007 || ''Premalekha Rasa'' || Sandya || Telugu ||\n|-\n| ''[[Kattradhu Thamizh]]'' || Anandhi || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||[[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut \u2013 South]]<br /> [[Vijay Award for Best Debu