ha-garage-maheshinte-prathikaram-and-kirik-party-lead-4683082/|publisher=The Indian Express|accessdate=1 April 2018|date=31 May 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n| rowspan=\"11\" |''[[K.G.F: Chapter 1|KGF : Chapter 1]]''\n|Filmibeat\n|Best Actor \u2013 Kannada\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |2019\n|[[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kanndiga]]\n|Best Actor - Kannada\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[SIIMA]]\n|Best Actor- Kannada \n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[SIIMA]]\n|Style Icon of South India\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Dadasaheb Phalke Award|Dadasaheb Phalke Award South]]\n|Outstanding Performance Of The Year\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[GQ50]]\n|Most Influential Young Indian\n|{{Won}}\n||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gqindia.com/influence-list/content/the-gq-50-most-influential-young-indians-of-2019|title=Here's the full list of GQ's 50 most influential young Indians of 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Siddashri National Award\n|Achievement In Social Service\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Kannada Kala Bhushana\n|Achievement In Cinema\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|BehindWoods Gold Medal\n|The Sensation Of South Indian Cinema\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Tv9 Kannada\n|Nava Nakshatra\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Awards South]]\n|Best Actor - Kannada\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/winners-of-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-38163.html|title=Winners of the 66th Filmfare Awards (South) 2019|website=filmfare.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{{commons category|Yash}}\n\n===Footnotes===\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|5232139|Yash}}\n* {{Instagram|thenameisyash}}\n* {{Twitter|TheNameIsYash}}\n* {{Facebook|TheOfficialYash}}\n{{FilmfareKannadaBestActor}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Actor}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yash}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Kannada playback singers]]\n[[Category:Kannada male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Mysore]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Yash\n| image              = Yash kgf event.jpg\n| caption            = Yash at ''K.G.F: Chapter 1'' film event\n| birth_name         = Naveen Kumar Gowda<ref name=\"Yash2\"/>\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|01|08}}<ref name=\"Yashh\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Yash|title=Yash: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday {{!}} eTimes|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Boovanahalli]], [[Hassan District]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]<ref name=\"Yashh\"/>\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| spouse             = [[Radhika Pandit]]\n| children           = 2\n| yearsactive        = 2007\u2013present \n| website            = {{website | nimmayash.in }}\n}}\n'''Naveen Kumar Gowda''', known by his [[stage name]] as '''Yash''', is an Indian film actor from [[Kannada cinema]]. He is known for his roles in the movies [[Rajadhani (2011 film)|Rajadhani]], [[Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari]], [[Kirataka]], [[K.G.F: Chapter 1]]. His latest film [[K.G.F: Chapter 2]] is scheduled to be released on October 23,2020.<ref name=\"Yash2\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/did-you-know/Yashs-real-name-revelaed/articleshow/29442760.cms|title=Who is Naveen Kumar Gowda in Sandalwood? - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Yash looking for success|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/25876.html|publisher=Indiaglitz|date=6 October 2006}}</ref><ref name=soaps>{{cite news|title= Yash honed his acting skills in theatre|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/did-you-know-/Yash-honed-his-acting-skills-in-theatre/articleshow/40574408.cms|work=The Times of India|date= 21 August 2014}}</ref> \n\nYash made his feature film debut with Jambada Hudugi and then  ''[[Moggina Manasu]]'' (2008), he played the male lead opposite then future wife Radhika. The film was a success and earned him the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]]. He went on to star in many commercially successful films including ''[[Modalasala]]'' (2010), Rajadhani (2011) ''[[Kirataka]]'' (2011), ''[[Drama (2012 film)|Drama]]'' (2012), ''[[Googly (film)|Googly]]'' (2013), ''[[Raja Huli]]'' (2013), ''[[Gajakesari]]'' (2014), ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari]]'' (2014), ''[[Masterpiece (2015 film)|Masterpiece]]'' (2015) and  ''[[K.G.F: Chapter 1]]'' (2018).\nHis rise to success has been well documented by the media, and he has been rated one of the popular actors in [[South India]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SUDEEP, RADHIKA EMERGE AS TOP SANDALWOOD ACTORS|url=http://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/south-masala/sudeep-radhika-emerge-as-top-sandalwood-actors/articleshow/56299692.cms|publisher=Bangalore Mirror|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=These hunks are the most desired men|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/these-hunks-are-the-most-desired-men/articleshow/56759564.cms|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nNaveen Kumar Gowda was born on 8 January 1986. He was born to [[Kannada]] speaking community in Bhuvanahalli is a village near by Hassan city [[Hassan district]] of Karnataka.<ref>{{cite AV media|date=23 August 2014|title=Weekend With Ramesh \u2013 Episode 7 \u2013 August 23, 2014|language=Kannada|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c2s-fRffpUo|accessdate=26 January 2017|time=2:50|quote=Naveen Kumar Gowda was born on 8 January 1986 in a government hospital in Bhuvanahalli in Hassan district to Arun Kumar J. and Pushpa}}</ref> His father, Arun Kumar J. worked in the [[Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation|KSRTC]] transport service, and later in the [[Bangalore Metropolitan Transport Corporation|BMTC]] transport service as a driver, and his mother, Pushpa latha, is a homemaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritykick.com/kannada-actor/yash-family|title=Actor Yash family, childhood photos|publisher=Celebritykick|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> He has a younger sister, Nandini. His childhood days were spent in [[Mysore]], where he did his pre university course (PUC) in Mahajana Education Society (MES),<ref>https://www.deccanherald.com/content/127219/a-hero-childhood.html</ref> and after finishing his studies, he joined the Benaka drama troupe which was formed by noted dramatist [[B. V. Karanth]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Yash honed his acting skills in theatre|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/did-you-know-/Yash-honed-his-acting-skills-in-theatre/articleshow/40574408.cms|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=26 January 2017|date=21 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Early days===\nYash started his acting career with the teleserial ''Nanda Gokula'' directed by Ashok Kashyap, which aired on [[ETV Network|ETV Kannada]]. He went on to appear in several other teleserials such as ''Malebillu'' and ''Preeti Illada Mele''.<ref name=serial1>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2013/kannada-television-artistes-films-116544.html|title=Kannada Television Artistes Who Made It Big In Films|publisher=filmibeat |date=7 August 2013|accessdate=23 August 2014}}</ref>  He had a small role in a 2007 film directed by Priya Hassan, ''Jambhada Hudugi''. He then acted in ''[[Moggina Manasu]]'' directed by [[Shashank (director)|Shashank]] in 2008, where he appeared in a supporting role alongside his ''Nanda Gokula'' co-star [[Radhika Pandit]]. He won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]] for his performance in the film.<ref>[http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2009/moggina-manasu-filmfare-030809.html Moggina Manasu bags five Filmfare awards]. Filmibeat (3 August 2009). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> Yash then starred in lead characters in the films ''[[Rocky (2008 film)|Rocky]]'' (2008), ''[[Kallara Santhe]]'' (2009), ''[[Gokula (film)|Gokula]]'' (2009).\n\nIn 2010, Yash starred in ''[[Modalasala]]'' which became his first commercial solo hit. His next film was ''[[Rajadhani (2011 film)|Rajadhani]]'' in 2011, which got good reviews<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/rajadhani-kannada-movie-review-12070.html Rajadhani review. Rajadhani Kannada movie review, story, rating]. IndiaGlitz.com (3 June 2011). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> and his performance was critically acclaimed<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/Rajadhani/movie-review/12173006.cms Rajadhani Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com. Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> although the film's return was below average at the box office. The same year, his next film ''[[Kirataka]]'' was a commercial success. Yash received positive reviews<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-kirataka/20110627.htm Review: Kirataka is a breezy entertainer \u2013 Rediff.com Movies]. Rediff.com (27 June 2011). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> for his performance in the village comedy film.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/Kirathaka/movie-review/9001473.cms Kirathaka Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com. Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/kirathaka-kannada-movie-review-13105.html Kirathaka review. Kirathaka Kannada movie review, story, rating]. IndiaGlitz.com (25 June 2011). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> In 2012 Yash had two major releases, ''[[Lucky (2012 Kannada film)|Lucky]]'' (opposite [[Ramya]]) and ''[[Jaanu]]'', both of which met with mixed response<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-lucky-is-a-treat-to-watch/20120224.htm Review: Lucky is a treat to watch \u2013 Rediff.com Movies]. Rediff.com (24 February 2012). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> upon release and became average grossers at the box office.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/Lucky/movie-review/12021694.cms Lucky Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (24 February 2012). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/Jaanu/movie-review/13706400.cms Jaanu Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (1 June 2012). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.ibnlive.com/news/india/kannada-review-jaanu-is-worth-a-watch-480445.html Kannada Review: 'Jaanu' is worth a watch \u2013 News18]. Ibnlive.com (3 June 2012). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref> His next film of the same year, the romantic comedy ''[[Drama (2012 film)|Drama]]'' directed by [[Yograj Bhat]] was a commercial success. The film was one of the major grossers of 2012.<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/88697.html It is over flow for DRAMA \u2013 Kannada Movie News]. Indiaglitz.com (30 November 2012). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132016: Success and stardom===\nIn his first release of 2013, ''[[Googly (film)|Googly]]'', a romance-drama, apart from a special appearance in a song sequence in ''[[Chandra (film)|Chandra]]''<ref>{{cite news|last1=Talukdar|first1=Taniya|title=Googly is unpredictable: Yash|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Googly-is-unpredictable-Yash/articleshow/21212599.cms|accessdate=4 July 2017|work=The Times of India|date=21 July 2013}}</ref> who falls for Swati (played by [[Kriti Kharbanda]]). Directed by [[Pavan Wadeeyar]], the film performed well, and was one among the highest-grossing Kannada films of the year.<ref>{{cite web|author=S. Shiva Kumar|title=How different are they?|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/how-different-are-they/article5071447.ece|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=4 July 2017|date=29 August 2013}}</ref> In 2014, he starred in ''[[Gajakesari]]'', which was directed by Krisha, and became commercially successful at the box office.<ref name = gajakesari>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2014/gajakesari-manam-affect-kochadaiyaan-box-office-collection-bangalore-142137.html|title=Gajakesari, Manam Affect Kochadaiyaan\u2019s Box Office Collection At Bangalore |publisher=filmibeat |date= 1 June 2014 |accessdate=23 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nYash's next film ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari]]'' opposite Radhika Pandit had its theatrical release on 25 December 2014, and opened to positive reviews and collected an estimated {{INR}}50<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/content-over-star-power-story-of-south-cinema-in-first-half-of-2015/story-KaqHkEArfSnQWbN6iJ5dCI.html|title=Content over star power: Story of south cinema in first half of 2015|date=2015-07-01|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> crore and went on to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest grossing]] Kannada cinema, and which made him one of the highest-paid actors in [[Kannada cinema|Sandalwood]].<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-pk-mr-mrs-ramachari-dominate-bengaluru-collection-centres-619818 Box Office Collection: 'PK', 'Mr & Mrs Ramachari' Dominate Bengaluru Collection Centres]. Ibtimes.co.in (9 January 2015). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/birthday-gift-to-yash-ramachari-to-enter-20-cr-club-soon-news-kannada-pbikMujcjecag.html|title=Birthday gift to Yash: Ramachari to enter cr club soon!|agency=www.sify.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= 'Mr and Mrs Ramachari' Review: Audience Live Response |url= http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mr-mrs-ramachari-review-audience-live-response-618291 |publisher= ibtimes.co.in |date= 25 December 2014 |accessdate= 2 January 2015}}</ref>\nIn 2015, he acted in ''[[Masterpiece (2015 film)|Masterpiece]]'', which opened to mixed reviews by the critics and emerged as a commercial hit at the box office.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/masterpiece-movie-review-live-audience-response-660740 Masterpiece movie review: Live audience response \u2013 IBTimes India]. Ibtimes.co.in (24 December 2015). Retrieved on 30 September 2018.</ref> In 2016, he starred in ''[[Santhu Straight Forward]]'' which performed fairly well at the box-office by collecting \u20b930 [[crore]].<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/santhu-straight-forward-box-office-collection-yash-radhika-starrer-hit-by-demonetisation-706471 Santhu Straight Forward box office collection: Yash-Radhika-starrer hit by demonetisation \u2013 IBTimes India]. Ibtimes.co.in (1 December 2016). Retrieved on 30 September 2018.</ref>\n\n===2018\u2013present===\nIn 2018 he starred in ''[[KGF (film)|KGF]]'', which was released in Kannada along with dubbed versions in Hindi, Telugu, Tamil, and Malayalam, had the highest production budget in the [[Kannada cinema]] industry, and emerging as highest Grossing film in kannada industry, collecting over \u20b9250 crore.<ref>[http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/apr/04/kgf-rockets-through-every-budget-barrier-1589884--1.html KGF rockets through every budget barrier]. The New Indian Express. Retrieved on 30 September 2018.</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIt was speculated in the media that Yash had been in a relationship with actress Radhika for long, and especially after their film, ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari]]'', that saw them portray the lead pair, and their third time together in films.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yash's mom ready to take care of his wife!|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Yashs-mom-ready-to-take-care-of-his-wife/articleshow/46426190.cms|accessdate=30 October 2016|work=The Times of India|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> Before the two disclosed it in public, their [[engagement]] took place in Goa on 12 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Actors Yash and Radhika get engaged in Goa|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kannada-actors-yash-and-radhika-get-engaged/1/738943.html|accessdate=30 October 2016|work=India Today|date=12 August 2016}}</ref> They married on 9 December 2016 in a private ceremony in [[Bangalore]], while Yash had openly invited everyone from [[Karnataka]] for their reception at [[Bangalore Palace]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kannada actors Yash and Radhika Pandit tie the knot in a dream wedding, see pics|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/kannada-actors-yash-and-radhika-pandit-tie-the-knot-in-a-dream-wedding-see-pics-4418875/|publisher=The Indian Express|accessdate=26 January 2017|date=9 December 2016}}</ref> Their first child, a baby girl Ayra was born on 2 December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/south/inside-yash-and-radhika-pandit-s-daughter-ayra-s-1st-grand-birthday-bash-check-it-out-489869|title=Inside Yash and Radhika Pandit\u2019s daughter Ayra\u2019s 1st grand birthday bash; Check it out|website=PINKVILLA|language=en|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> Their second child, a baby boy was born on 30 October 2019.\n\n==Other work==\nIn 2017 Yash along with his [[actress]] wife [[Radhika Pandit]] founded an organization and named it as Yasho Marga Foundation which marks their contribution towards the betterment of the [[society]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/yash-and-radhika-pandits-new-foundation/articleshow/56968999.cms|title=There's something new in Yash and Radhika Pandit's life|publisher=The Times of India|date=26 February 2017}}</ref> As a first step, the foundation took up the water crisis issue in [[Koppal]] district of [[Karnataka]] by reportedly investing {{INR}}4 crores towards the desiltation of the lakes and providing pure drinking water to the drought affected areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/yasho-marga-yashassu-yash-dilkush-kannada-news-182344|title=Yasho Marga Yashassu, Yash dilkush|publisher=Indiaglitz|date=29 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\u2022 '' All the films are in [[Kannada]] language, unless otherwise noted. ''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Director(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2007\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Jambada Hudugi''\n|{{Unknown}}\n|\n| Uncredited\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2008\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Moggina Manasu]]''\n| Rahul \n|[[Shashank (director)|Shashank]]\n|Debut film\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |last1=Vijayasarathy |first1=R. G. |title=Moggina Manasu works |url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/jul/21ssmm.htm |website=Rediff.com |accessdate=28 December 2018 |date=21 July 2008}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Rocky (2008 film)|Rocky]]''\n| Rocky \n| S. K. Nagendra Urs\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2009\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Kallara Santhe]]''\n| Somu\n|[[Sumana Kittur]]\n|\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Gokula (film)|Gokula]]''\n| Raja \n|[[Prakash (film director)|Prakash]]\n| \n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2010\n! scope=\"row\"| 