s-of-2018.html|title=The Best Albums of 2018|publisher=[[Okayplayer]]|date=December 21, 2018|accessdate=December 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181221121315/https://www.okayplayer.com/music/what-were-the-best-albums-of-2018.html|archive-date=December 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|23}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-50-best-albums-of-2018/?page=3|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2018|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=December 11, 2018|accessdate=December 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211131624/https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-50-best-albums-of-2018/?page=3|archive-date=December 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| 50 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|6}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-albums-2018-764071/travis-scott-astroworld-764114/|title=50 Best Albums of 2018|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=December 13, 2018|accessdate=December 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215022243/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-albums-2018-764071/travis-scott-astroworld-764114/|archive-date=December 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Uproxx]]\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|1}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-of-2018-ranked/|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2018|publisher=[[Uproxx]]|date=December 3, 2018|accessdate=December 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205103606/https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-of-2018-ranked/|archive-date=December 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| The Best Albums of the 2010s\n| {{center|20}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-2010s-ranked-decade/|title=The Best Albums of the 2010s, Ranked|publisher=Uproxx|date=October 7, 2019|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]''\n| 30 Best Albums of 2018\n| {{center|28}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/photos/best-albums-2018-list/travis-scott-astroworld-album-cover-1545005066|title=30 Best Albums of 2018|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|date=December 18, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181219134542/https://www.vibe.com/photos/best-albums-2018-list/travis-scott-astroworld-album-cover-1545005066|archive-date=December 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"4\"| 2019\n| [[American Music Awards of 2019|American Music Awards]]\n| [[American Music Award for Favorite Rap/Hip-Hop Album|Favorite Album \u2013 Rap/Hip-Hop]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/american-music-awards-full-list-winners-2018-1146665/item/favorite-male-artist-soul-r-b-1142148|title=American Music Awards: Taylor Swift Wins Artist of the Year, Sets New Record|work=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Nordyke|first=Kimberly|date=October 9, 2018|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2019 BET Hip Hop Awards|BET Hip Hop Awards]]\n| [[BET Hip Hop Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8532511/bet-hip-hop-awards-2019-complete-winners-list|title=BET Hip Hop Awards 2019: Complete Winners List|work=Billboard|date=October 8, 2019|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2019 Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]]\n| [[Billboard Music Award for Top Billboard 200 Album|Top ''Billboard'' 200 Album]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8509655/billboard-music-awards-2019-winners-list|title=2019 Billboard Music Awards Winners: The Complete List|website=Billboard|last=Lynch|first=Joe|date=May 1, 2019|accessdate=June 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516041948/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8509655/billboard-music-awards-2019-winners-list|archive-date=May 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[61st Annual Grammy Awards|Grammy Award]]s\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/2019-grammys-winners-list-1203131935/|title=2019 Grammys Winners List|work=Variety|author=Variety Staff|date=February 10, 2019|accessdate=February 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211011648/https://variety.com/2019/music/news/2019-grammys-winners-list-1203131935/|archive-date=February 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nIn Travis Scott's home country of the United States, ''Astroworld'' debuted at number one on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 537,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, which included 270,000 pure album sales.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8469748/travis-scott-astroworld-no-1-billboard-200-album-chart|title=Travis Scott's 'Astroworld' Bows at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart With Second-Largest Debut of 2018|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=August 12, 2018|accessdate=August 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812225606/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8469748/travis-scott-astroworld-no-1-billboard-200-album-chart|archive-date=August 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The album scored the second-largest first week of the year, behind ''[[Scorpion (Drake album)|Scorpion]]'' by [[Drake (musician)|Drake]], and second-largest pure album sales week of the year, behind [[Dave Matthews Band]]'s ''[[Come Tomorrow (album)|Come Tomorrow]]''.<ref name=\"Billboard\" /> The album earned 349.43&nbsp;million streams in the first week, marking fifth largest streaming week ever.<ref name=\"Billboard\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.48006/title.hip-hop-album-sales-travis-scotts-astroworld-dethrones-drake-with-epic-no-1-billboard-200-debut|title=Hip Hop Album Sales: Travis Scott's \"Astroworld\" Dethrones Drake With Epic No. 1 Billboard 200 Debut|work=HipHopDX|last=Eustice|first=Kyle|date=August 13, 2018|accessdate=August 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814040635/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.48006/title.hip-hop-album-sales-travis-scotts-astroworld-dethrones-drake-with-epic-no-1-billboard-200-debut|archive-date=August 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It serves as Scott's second number-one album in the United States.<ref name=\"Billboard\" /> Following the release, all 17 tracks on the album entered the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], including \"[[Sicko Mode]]\" (at 4) and \"Stargazing\" (8), which made Scott the fourth act to have debuted multiple songs in the chart's top 10 simultaneously.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8469837/drake-in-my-feelings-travis-scott-debuts-hot-100|title=Drake Rules Billboard Hot 100 for Fifth Week With 'In My Feelings,' Travis Scott Debuts Two Songs in Top 10|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=August 13, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813210704/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8469837/drake-in-my-feelings-travis-scott-debuts-hot-100|archive-date=August 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The album earned 205,000 album-equivalent units in the second week, staying at number one.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8470929/travis-scott-astroworld-no-1-second-week-billboard-200|title=Travis Scott's 'Astroworld' Spends Second Week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|work=Billboard|date=August 19, 2018|accessdate=August 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820005920/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8470929/travis-scott-astroworld-no-1-second-week-billboard-200|archive-date=August 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 3, 2018, ''Astroworld'' returned to the number-one spot on the ''Billboard'' 200, earning 71,000 album-equivalent units, almost four months after its initial release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8487688/travis-scott-astroworld-returns-to-no-1-billboard-200|title=Travis Scott's 'Astroworld' Returns to No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart, 6ix9ine's 'Dummy Boy' Debuts at No. 2|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|work=Billboard|date=December 2, 2018|accessdate=December 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203071129/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8487688/travis-scott-astroworld-returns-to-no-1-billboard-200|archive-date=December 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of 2018, the album has earned over 1,985,000 album-equivalent units in the US, with over 464,000 being pure sales, marking the second best-selling hip hop in pure album sales of the year, behind only [[Eminem]]'s ''[[Kamikaze (Eminem album)|Kamikaze]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8492663/nielsen-music-top-album-2018-drake-scorpion|title=Nielsen Music's Top Album of 2018 in US Is Drake's 'Scorpion'|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=January 8, 2019|accessdate=February 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190202234015/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8492663/nielsen-music-top-album-2018-drake-scorpion|archive-date=February 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Scorpion BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryanrolli/2018/10/23/eminem-kamikaze-platinum-bestselling-rap-album-2018/#2eedff97255c|title=Eminem's 'Kamikaze' Is Eligible For Platinum, Becomes Bestselling 'Pure' Rap Album of 2018|work=Forbes|last=Rolli|first=Bryan|date=October 23, 2018|accessdate=October 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025190750/https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryanrolli/2018/10/23/eminem-kamikaze-platinum-bestselling-rap-album-2018/#2eedff97255c|archive-date=October 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 25, 2019, ''Astroworld'' was certified [[RIAA certification|triple platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) with three million album-equivalent units in the United States.<ref name=\"RIAA\" />\n\nIn Australia, ''Astroworld'' opened atop the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums Chart]], becoming Travis Scott's first number-one on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/travis-scott-scores-debut-1-with-astroworld|title=Travis Scott scores debut No. 1 with Astroworld|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|accessdate=August 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812083024/https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/travis-scott-scores-debut-1-with-astroworld|archive-date=August 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Two tracks \"Sicko Mode\" (at 7) and \"Stargazing\" (10) charted in the top ten of the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]], marking the rapper's first top ten songs in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/drake-s-in-my-feelings-holds-1-for-fourth-week|title=Drake's in My Feelings holds No. 1 for fourth week|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|accessdate=August 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812053942/https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/drake-s-in-my-feelings-holds-1-for-fourth-week|archive-date=August 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In Canada, ''Astroworld'' moved 27,000 album-equivalent units in its opening week.<ref name=\"Fyi\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/08/13/drake-unseated-no-1-travis-scotts-astroworld|title=Drake Unseated From No. 1 By Travis Scott's 'Astroworld'|publisher=FYIMusicNews|accessdate=August 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813210527/https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/08/13/drake-unseated-no-1-travis-scotts-astroworld|archive-date=August 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It serves as Scott's first number-one album in the country.<ref name=\"Fyi\" /> In the second week, the album earned 13,000 album-equivalent units, marking the second straight week at the top of the [[Canadian Albums Chart|''Billboard'' Canadian Albums]].<ref name=\"Fyi2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/08/20/arethas-30-greatest-hits-has-chart-comeback|title=Aretha's '30 Greatest Hits' Has A Chart Comeback|publisher=FYIMusicNews|accessdate=August 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820172748/https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/08/20/arethas-30-greatest-hits-has-chart-comeback|archive-date=August 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, the album debuted at number three on the [[UK Albums Chart]], becoming the rapper's first top ten album on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/travis-scotts-astroworld-scores-highest-new-entry-on-official-albums-chart__23588/|title=Travis Scott's Astroworld scores highest new entry on Official Albums Chart|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=August 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811032306/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/travis-scotts-astroworld-scores-highest-new-entry-on-official-albums-chart__23588/|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> As well as the album, the three tracks \"Sicko Mode\" (at 9), \"Stargazing\" (15), and \"Carousel\" (29) charted in the top 40 of the [[UK Singles Chart]], while the lead single \"[[Butterfly Effect (Travis Scott song)|Butterfly Effect]]\" previously reached number 57 on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2018/08/10/travis-scott-tyga-and-offset-collect-new-top-10-singles-in-the-u-k/|title=Travis Scott, Tyga And Offset Collect New Top 10 Singles in the U.K.|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=August 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810193755/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2018/08/10/travis-scott-tyga-and-offset-collect-new-top-10-singles-in-the-u-k/|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\nCredits were adapted from the album's liner notes, [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] and [[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]].<ref name=\"LN\">{{cite AV media notes|title=Astroworld|type=CD liner notes|others=[[Travis Scott]] | publisher=[[Epic Records]] | year=2018|id=88362-5}}</ref><ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/92967282|title=ASTROWORLD / Travis Scott on TIDAL|publisher=Tidal|accessdate=August 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803104056/https://listen.tidal.com/album/92967282|archive-date=August 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/StartPage.aspx|title=BMI {{!}} Repertoire Search|publisher=BMI|accessdate=May 8, 2019|at=Select \"TITLE\", type \"Song\" in the search engine, and click \"Search\".|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406022825/http://repertoire.bmi.com/StartPage.aspx|archive-date=April 6, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = 58:33\n\n| title1 = [[Stargazing (Travis Scott song)|Stargazing]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Travis Scott|Jacques Webster]]|[[Sonny Digital|Sonny Uwaezuoke]]|[[Bkorn|Brandon Korn]]|Brandon Whitfield|[[30 Roc|Samuel Gloade]]|[[Cyhi the Prynce|Cydel Young]]|Jamie Lepe|[[Mike Dean (record producer)|Michael Dean]]|Lamont Porter}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|[[Sonny Digital]]|B Wheezy|[[Bkor