bums produced by Allen Ritter]]\n[[Category:Cactus Jack Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "TheAmazingPeanuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astroworld_(album)"}
{"title_page": "Pie-O-My", "text_new": "{{Infobox television episode\n| title          = Pie-O-My\n| series         = [[The Sopranos]]\n| caption        = Tony, Ralph, Silvio, and Hesh celebrate a victory by Ralph's new racehorse, Pie-O-My.\n| season         = 4\n| episode        = 5\n| guests         = ''see below''\n| airdate        = October 13, 2002\n| length         = 54 minutes\n| editor         = \n| production     = 405\n| writer         = [[Robin Green]]<br />[[Mitchell Burgess]]\n| director       = [[Henry J. Bronchtein]]\n| photographer   = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list   = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 4)\n| image          = Sopranos ep405.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| prev           = [[The Weight (The Sopranos)|The Weight]]\n| next           = [[Everybody Hurts (The Sopranos)|Everybody Hurts]]\n}}\n\"'''Pie-O-My'''\" is the 44th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the fifth of the show's fourth season. Written by [[Robin Green]] and [[Mitchell Burgess]], and directed by [[Henry J. Bronchtein]], it originally aired on October 13, 2002.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] *\n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]] \n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]] *\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] *\n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]] *\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]]\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Steven R. Schirripa]] as [[Bobby Baccalieri]]\n* and [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]]\n*Pie O My /Goldee bred and owned by Kimberly Martin\n\n===Guest starring===\n* [[Jerry Adler]] as [[Hesh Rabkin]]\n\n====Also guest starring====\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Matthew Del Negro]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Brian Cammarata|Brian Cammarata]]\n* [[Robert Funaro]] as [[Eugene Pontecorvo]]\n* [[Joseph R. Gannascoli]] as [[Vito Spatafore]]\n* [[Lola Glaudini]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Deborah Ciccerone Waldrup|Agent Deborah Ciccerone]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* [[Arthur J. Nascarella]] as [[Carlo Gervasi]]\n* [[Richard Portnow]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Harold Melvoin|Harold Melvoin]]\n* [[Michele Santopietro]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#JoJo Palmice|JoJo Palmice]]\n* [[Matt Servitto]] as [[Dwight Harris|Agent Harris]]\n* [[Karen Young (actress)|Karen Young]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Sanseverino]]\n* Angelo Massagli as [[List of characters from The Sopranos \u2013 friends and family#Robert .22Bobby.22 Baccalieri III|Bobby Baccalieri III]]\n* Lexie Sperduto as [[List of characters from The Sopranos \u2013 friends and family#Sophia Baccalieri|Sophia Baccalieri]]\n* Stewart J. Zully as Alan Ginsberg\n* Val Bisoglio as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Murf Lupo|Murf Lupo]]\n* David Copeland as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Joseph .22Joey.22 Cogo|Joey Cogo]]\n* Manon Halliburton as Lois Pettit, the horse trainer\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\n\n[[Adriana La Cerva|Adriana]] realizes that her club is not hers: the back rooms are freely used by [[Tony Soprano|Tony]] and his crew for business. Her [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]  handlers, including her new contact [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Robyn Sanseverino]], are pressing for information. They tell her that [[Christopher Moltisanti|Christopher]] is associating with dangerous criminals, and she can help him; they cause her to doubt what she believes, that [[Richie Aprile|Richie]] and [[Pussy Bonpensiero|Pussy]] disappeared because they entered [[witness protection]]. She gives away a little information about [[Patsy Parisi|Patsy]]. At home, she relieves stress with an injection of Chris' [[heroin]].\n\n[[Janice Soprano|Janice]] is insinuating herself into [[Bobby Baccalieri|Bobby]]'s family life. She freezes out  [[Mikey Palmice]]'s widow [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#JoJo Palmice|JoJo]]. She serves the family [[Carmela Soprano|Carmela]]'s delicious [[lasagna]], claiming it as her own. She urges Bobby to get over his grief\u2014he might lose [[Junior Soprano|Junior]]'s support. Bobby pulls himself together and completes a neglected task for Junior: meeting with a [[labor union|union]] [[shop steward]] to intimidate him into changing his vote in an upcoming election. \n\nTony and Carmela are still bitterly divided about money and investment. He refuses to sign the  [[life insurance trust]] she proposes, having been advised it is too much in her favor. She receives a stock tip; when he comes up with the money, it is too late.\n\n[[Ralph Cifaretto|Ralphie]]'s [[racehorse]], \"Pie-O-My\", wins and he happily shares the winnings with Tony. Next time Tony, who has suggested the race tactics, requires an even bigger share, to Ralphie's chagrin. Tony begins to speak of \"our\" horse; Ralphie is less fond and resents the expense.  [[Veterinarian]]'s fees pile up, and one night when Pie-O-My is very sick the vet refuses further treatment unless he is paid. Ralphie refuses to act and passes along Tony's number; Tony rushes to the stables and pays. Then he goes into the stall and sits with the animal, gently stroking her neck, telling her that everything will be all right.\n\n==First appearances==\n* [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Robyn Sanseverino]]: The F.B.I. agent assigned to handle Adriana.\n\n==Title reference==\n*The episode's title is the name of Ralph's race horse, Pie-O-My.\n\n==References to other media or events==\n* At the stables, Hesh references [[Seabiscuit]], who was, at the time, a frequent [[popular culture|pop culture]] reference due to the popularity of [[Seabiscuit: An American Legend|the book about him]]. This episode aired before the release of the [[Seabiscuit (film)|2003 motion picture]] of the same name.\n* In a scene where Adriana was at home watching television, she was watching a ''[[Jake Steinfeld|Body by Jake]]'' [[infomercial]].\n\n==Music==\n* The song played over the end credits is \"My Rifle, My Pony and Me\" by [[Dean Martin]] and [[Ricky Nelson]], from the 1959 Western ''[[Rio Bravo (film)|Rio Bravo]]''. Tony is seen watching this movie (and specifically, the scene in which the song appears) in the Season Four premiere, \"[[For All Debts Public and Private]]\".\n* The song heard from A.J.'s room when Tony is in bed is \"The Gift That Keeps On Giving\" by [[Deicide (band)|Deicide]] from their album ''[[Insineratehymn]]''.\n* [[Snake River Conspiracy]]'s cover of [[The Cure]]'s [[Lovesong (The Cure song)|Lovesong]] plays in the Crazy Horse club.\n* The song played when Bobby goes into Dorley's Lounge to speak with Teddy about the union vote is \"[[Theme for an Imaginary Western]]\" by [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]].\n* The song playing in the Crazy Horse club when Adrianna walks in on Tony and Ralph in her office is \"Can't Stand It\" by [[The Greenhornes]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/index.html#/the-sopranos/episodes/4/44-pie-o-my/index.html \"Pie-O-My\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705271}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/pie-o-my-192234}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pie-O-My}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 4) episodes]]\n[[Category:2002 American television episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television episode\n| title = Pie-O-My\n| series = [[The Sopranos]]\n| season = 4\n| episode = 5\n| guests= ''see below''\n| airdate = October 13, 2002\n| length = 54 minutes\n| production = 405\n| writer = [[Robin Green]]<br />[[Mitchell Burgess]]\n| director = [[Henry J. Bronchtein]]\n| photographer = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 4)\n| image = Sopranos ep405.jpg\n| image_size = 300px\n| prev = [[The Weight (The Sopranos)|The Weight]]\n| next = [[Everybody Hurts (The Sopranos)|Everybody Hurts]]\n}}\n\"'''Pie-O-My'''\" is the 44th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the fifth of the show's fourth season. Written by [[Robin Green]] and [[Mitchell Burgess]], and directed by [[Henry J. Bronchtein]], it originally aired on October 13, 2002.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] *\n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]] \n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]] *\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] *\n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]] *\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]]\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Steven R. Schirripa]] as [[Bobby Baccalieri]]\n* and [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]]\n*Pie O My /Goldee bred and owned by Kimberly Martin\n\n===Guest starring===\n* [[Jerry Adler]] as [[Hesh Rabkin]]\n\n====Also guest starring====\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Matthew Del Negro]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Brian Cammarata|Brian Cammarata]]\n* [[Robert Funaro]] as [[Eugene Pontecorvo]]\n* [[Joseph R. Gannascoli]] as [[Vito Spatafore]]\n* [[Lola Glaudini]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Deborah Ciccerone Waldrup|Agent Deborah Ciccerone]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* [[Arthur J. Nascarella]] as [[Carlo Gervasi]]\n* [[Richard Portnow]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Harold Melvoin|Harold Melvoin]]\n* [[Michele Santopietro]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#JoJo Palmice|JoJo Palmice]]\n* [[Matt Servitto]] as [[Dwight Harris|Agent Harris]]\n* [[Karen Young (actress)|Karen Young]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Sanseverino]]\n* Angelo Massagli as [[List of characters from The Sopranos \u2013 friends and family#Robert .22Bobby.22 Baccalieri III|Bobby Baccalieri III]]\n* Lexie Sperduto as [[List of characters from The Sopranos \u2013 friends and family#Sophia Baccalieri|Sophia Baccalieri]]\n* Stewart J. Zully as Alan Ginsberg\n* Val Bisoglio as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Murf Lupo|Murf Lupo]]\n* David Copeland as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Joseph .22Joey.22 Cogo|Joey Cogo]]\n* Manon Halliburton as Lois Pettit, the horse trainer\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\n\n[[Adriana La Cerva|Adriana]] realizes that her club is not hers: the back rooms are freely used by [[Tony Soprano|Tony]] and his crew for business. Her [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]  handlers, including her new contact [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Robyn Sanseverino]], are pressing for information. They tell her that [[Christopher Moltisanti|Christopher]] is associating with dangerous criminals, and she can help him; they cause her to doubt what she believes, that [[Richie Aprile|Richie]] and [[Pussy Bonpensiero|Pussy]] disappeared because they entered [[witness protection]]. She gives away a little information about [[Patsy Parisi|Patsy]]. At home, she relieves stress with an injection of Chris' [[heroin]].\n\n[[Janice Soprano|Janice]] is insinuating herself into [[Bobby Baccalieri|Bobby]]'s family life. She freezes out  [[Mikey Palmice]]'s widow [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#JoJo Palmice|JoJo]]. She serves the family [[Carmela Soprano|Carmela]]'s delicious [[lasagna]], claiming it as her own. She urges Bobby to get over his grief\u2014he might lose [[Junior Soprano|Junior]]'s support. Bobby pulls himself together and completes a neglected task for Junior: meeting with a [[labor union|union]] [[shop steward]] to intimidate him into changing his vote in an upcoming election. \n\nTony and Carmela are still bitterly divided about money and investment. He refuses to sign the  [[life insurance trust]] she proposes, having been advised it is too much in her favor. She receives a stock tip; when he comes up with the money, it is too late.\n\n[[Ralph Cifaretto|Ralphie]]'s [[racehorse]], \"Pie-O-My\", wins and he happily shares the winnings with Tony. Next time Tony, who has suggested the race tactics, requires an even bigger share, to Ralphie's chagrin. Tony begins to speak of \"our\" horse; Ralphie is less fond and resents the expense.  [[Veterinarian]]'s fees pile up, and one night when Pie-O-My is very sick the vet refuses further treatment unless he is paid. Ralphie refuses to act and passes along Tony's number; Tony rushes to the stables and pays. Then he goes into the stall and sits with the animal, gently stroking her neck, telling her that everything will be all right.\n\n==First appearances==\n* [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Robyn Sanseverino]]: The F.B.I. agent assigned to handle Adriana.\n\n==Title reference==\n*The episode's title is the name of Ralph's race horse, Pie-O-My.\n\n==References to other media or events==\n* At the stables, Hesh references [[Seabiscuit]], who was, at the time, a frequent [[popular culture|pop culture]] reference due to the popularity of [[Seabiscuit: An American Legend|the book about him]]. This episode aired before the release of the [[Seabiscuit (film)|2003 motion picture]] of the same name.\n* In a scene where Adriana was at home watching television, she was watching a ''[[Jake Steinfeld|Body by Jake]]'' [[infomercial]].\n\n==Music==\n* The song played over the end credits is \"My Rifle, My Pony and Me\" by [[Dean Martin]] and [[Ricky Nelson]], from the 1959 Western ''[[Rio Bravo (film)|Rio Bravo]]''. Tony is seen watching this movie (and specifically, the scene in which the song appears) in the Season Four premiere, \"[[For All Debts Public and Private]]\".\n* The song heard from A.J.'s room when Tony is in bed is \"The Gift That Keeps On Giving\" by [[Deicide (band)|Deicide]] from their album ''[[Insineratehymn]]''.\n* [[Snake River Conspiracy]]'s cover of [[The Cure]]'s [[Lovesong (The Cure song)|Lovesong]] plays in the Crazy Horse club.\n* The song played when Bobby goes into Dorley's Lounge to speak with Teddy about the union vote is \"[[Theme for an Imaginary Western]]\" by [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]].\n* The song playing in the Crazy Horse club when Adrianna walks in on Tony and Ralph in her office is \"Can't Stand It\" by [[The Greenhornes]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/index.html#/the-sopranos/episodes/4/44-pie-o-my/index.html \"Pie-O-My\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705271}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/pie-o-my-192234}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pie-O-My}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 4) episodes]]\n[[Category:2002 American television episodes]]\n", "name_user": "Fullmetal2887", "label": "safe", "comment": "image caption", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pie-O-My"}
{"title_page": "QMA", "text_new": "{{about|the mathematical theory|the coaxial RF connector|QMA and QN connector}}\n\nIn [[computational complexity theory]], '''QMA''', which stands for '''Quantum [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|Merlin Arthur]]''', is the quantum analog of the nonprobabilistic [[complexity class]] [[NP (complexity)|NP]] or the probabilistic complexity class [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|MA]]. It is related to [[BQP]] in the same way [[NP (complexity)|NP]] is related to [[P (complexity)|P]], or [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|MA]] is related to [[Bounded-error probabilistic polynomial|BPP]].\n\nInformally, it is the set of [[decision problem]]s for which, when the answer is YES, there is a polynomial-size quantum proof (a quantum state) that convinces a polynomial-time quantum verifier of the fact with high probability. Moreover, when the answer is NO, every polynomial-size quantum state is rejected by the verifier with high probability.\n\nMore precisely, the proofs have to be verifiable in [[polynomial time]] on a [[quantum computer]], such that if the answer is indeed YES, the verifier accepts a correct proof with probability greater than 2/3, and if the answer is NO, then there is no proof which convinces the verifier to accept with probability greater than 1/3. As is usually the case, the constants 2/3 and 1/3 can be changed. Changing 2/3 to any constant strictly between 1/2 and 1, or changing 1/3 to any constant strictly between 0 and 1/2, does not change the class QMA.\n\n'''QAM''' is a related complexity class, in which fictional agents Arthur and Merlin carry out the sequence: Arthur generates a random string, Merlin answers with a quantum [[certificate (complexity)|certificate]] and Arthur verifies it as a BQP machine.\n\n== Definition ==\n\nA language L is in <math>\\mbox{QMA}(c,s)</math> if there exists a polynomial time quantum verifier V and a polynomial p(x) such that:<ref>{{cite arXiv|eprint=quant-ph/0210077v1|first1=Dorit|last1=Aharonov|author1-link= Dorit Aharonov|first2=Tomer|last2=Naveh|title=Quantum NP \u2013 A Survey|year=2002}}</ref><ref name=\"JW\">{{cite book|arxiv=0804.3401|first=John|last=Watrous|authorlink=John Watrous (computer scientist)|chapter=Quantum Computational Complexity|year=2009|title=Encyclopedia of Complexity and Systems Science|pages=7174\u20137201|doi=10.1007/978-0-387-30440-3_428|editor-first=Robert A.|editor-last=Meyers}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gharibian |first1=Sevag |last2=Huang |first2=Yichen |last3=Landau |first3=Zeph |last4=Shin |first4=Seung Woo |title=Quantum Hamiltonian Complexity |journal=Foundations and Trends in Theoretical Computer Science |date=2015 |volume=10 |issue=3 |pages=159\u2013282 |doi=10.1561/0400000066|arxiv=1401.3916 }}</ref>\n*<math>\\forall x \\in L</math>, there exists a quantum state <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math> such that the probability that V accepts the input <math>(|x\\rangle, |\\psi\\rangle)</math> is greater than <math>c</math>.\n*<math>\\forall x \\notin L</math>, for all quantum states <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math>, the probability that V accepts the input <math>(|x\\rangle, |\\psi\\rangle)</math> is less than <math>s</math>.\nwhere <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math> ranges over all quantum states with at most p(|x|) qubits.\n\nThe complexity class <math>\\mbox{QMA}</math> is defined to be equal to <math>\\mbox{QMA}({2}/{3},1/3)</math>. However, the constants are not too important since the class remains unchanged if <math>c</math> and <math>s</math> are set to any constants such that <math>c</math> is greater than <math>s</math>. Moreover, for any polynomials <math>q(n)</math> and <math>r(n)</math>, we have\n:<math>\\mbox{QMA}\\left(\\frac{2}{3},\\frac{1}{3}\\right) =\\mbox{QMA}\\left(\\frac{1}{2}+\\frac{1}{q(n)},\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{1}{q(n)}\\right)=\\mbox{QMA}(1-2^{-r(n)},2^{-r(n)})</math>.\n\n== Problems in QMA ==\n\nSince many interesting classes are contained in QMA, such as P, BQP and NP, all problems in those classes are also in QMA. However, there are problems that are in QMA but not known to be in NP or BQP. Some such well known problems are discussed below.\n\nA problem is said to be QMA-hard, analogous to [[NP-hard]], if every problem in QMA can be [[Reduction (complexity)|reduced]] to it. A problem is said to be QMA-[[complete (complexity)|complete]] if it is QMA-hard and in QMA.\n\n=== The local Hamiltonian problem ===\nThe local Hamiltonian problem is the quantum analogue of [[Maximum satisfiability problem|MAX-SAT]]. A Hamiltonian is a [[Hermitian matrix]] acting on quantum states, thus it is <math>2^n \\times 2^n</math> for a system of n [[qubit]]s. A k-local Hamiltonian is a Hamiltonian which can be written as the sum of Hamiltonians, each of which act non-trivially on at most k qubits (instead of all n qubits).\n\nThe k-local Hamiltonian problem, which is a [[promise problem]], is defined as follows. The input is a k-local Hamiltonian acting on n qubits, which is the sum of polynomially many Hermitian matrices that act on only k qubits. The input also contains two numbers <math>a< b \\in [0,1]</math>, such that <math>\\frac{1}{b-a}=O(n^c)</math> for some constant c. The problem is to determine whether the smallest eigenvalue of this Hamiltonian is less than <math>a</math> or greater than <math>b</math>, promised that one of these is the case.\n\nThe k-local Hamiltonian is QMA-complete for k \u2265 2.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Kempe | first1=Julia | author1-link = Julia Kempe | last2=Kitaev | first2=Alexei |author2-link= Alexei Kitaev | last3=Regev | first3=Oded | author3-link= Oded Regev | title=The complexity of the local Hamiltonian problem | year=2006 | journal=[[SIAM Journal on Computing]] | volume=35 | issue=5 | pages=1070\u20131097 | arxiv=quant-ph/0406180v2  | doi=10.1137/S0097539704445226}}.</ref>\n\nQMA-hardness results are known for even simplistic and physically realistic [[lattice models]] of [[qubits]] such as <ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Biamonte | first1=Jacob | last2=Love | first2=Peter | title=Realizable Hamiltonians for universal adiabatic quantum computers | journal=[[Physical Review A]] | year=2008 | volume=78 | issue=1 | pages=012352 | arxiv=0704.1287  | doi=10.1103/PhysRevA.78.012352 | bibcode=2008PhRvA..78a2352B}}.</ref>\n<math>\nH = \\sum_{i}h_i Z_i + \\sum_{i<j}J^{ij}Z_iZ_j + \\sum_{i<j}K^{ij}X_iX_j\n</math> \nwhere <math>Z, X</math> represent the [[Pauli matrices]] <math>\\sigma_z, \\sigma_x</math>.  Such models are applicable to universal [[adiabatic quantum computation]].\n\nThe Hamiltonians for the QMA-complete problem can also be restricted to act on a two dimensional grid of [[qubits]]<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Oliveira\n| first = Roberto\n|first2=Barbara M. | last2 = Terhal\n | title = The complexity of quantum spin systems on a two-dimensional square lattice\n| volume = 8\n| pages = 900\u2013924\n| journal = Quantum Information and Computation\n| year = 2008\n| issue = 10\n| arxiv = quant-ph/0504050\n| bibcode = 2005quant.ph..4050O\n}}</ref> or a line of quantum particles with 12 states per particle.<ref>{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1007/s00220-008-0710-3\n| volume = 287\n| issue = 1\n| pages = 41\u201365\n| last = Aharonov\n| first = Dorit | author1-link = Dorit Aharonov\n|first2=Daniel | last2 = Gottesman | author2-link = Daniel Gottesman |first3=Sandy | last3 = Irani |first4=Julia | last4= Kempe | author4-link = Julia Kempe\n | title = The power of quantum systems on a line\n| journal = [[Communications in Mathematical Physics]]\n| year = 2009 | bibcode=2009CMaPh.287...41A\n| arxiv= 0705.4077}}</ref>\n\n===Other QMA-complete problems===\nA list of known QMA-complete problems can be found at https://arxiv.org/abs/1212.6312.\n\n== Related classes ==\n\n'''QCMA''' (or '''MQA'''<ref name=\"JW\" />), which stands for Quantum Classical Merlin Arthur (or Merlin Quantum Arthur), is similar to QMA, but the proof has to be a classical string. It is not known whether QMA equals QCMA, although QCMA is clearly contained in QMA.\n\n'''QIP(k)''', which stands for [[Quantum Interactive Polynomial time]] (k messages), is a generalization of QMA where Merlin and Arthur can interact for k rounds. QMA is QIP(1). QIP(2) is known to be in PSPACE.<ref>{{Cite book | last1=Jain | first1=Rahul | last2=Upadhyay | first2=Sarvagya | last3=Watrous | first3=John | author3-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | title=[[Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science|Proceedings of the 50th Annual IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science (FOCS '09)]] | publisher=IEEE Computer Society | isbn=978-0-7695-3850-1 | year=2009 | chapter=Two-message quantum interactive proofs are in PSPACE | doi = 10.1109/FOCS.2009.30 | pages=534\u2013543}}</ref>\n\n'''[[QIP (complexity)|QIP]]''' is QIP(k) where k is allowed to be polynomial in the number of qubits. It is known that QIP(3) = QIP.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Watrous | first1=John | author1-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | title=PSPACE has constant-round quantum interactive proof systems | year=2003 | journal=[[Theoretical Computer Science (journal)|Theoretical Computer Science]] | volume=292 | issue=3 | pages=575\u2013588 | doi=10.1016/S0304-3975(01)00375-9 }}</ref> It is also known that QIP = [[IP (complexity)|IP]] = [[PSPACE]].<ref>{{cite journal | last1=Jain | first1=Rahul | last2=Ji | first2=Zhengfeng | last3=Upadhyay | first3=Sarvagya | last4=Watrous | first4=John | author4-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | journal = [[Journal of the ACM]] | year=2011 | title=QIP = PSPACE | volume = 58 | issue = 6 | page = A30 | doi = 10.1145/2049697.2049704}}\n</ref>\n\n== Relationship to other classes ==\n\nQMA is related to other known [[complexity classes]] by the following relations:\n:<math>\\mathsf{P} \\subseteq \\mathsf{NP} \\subseteq \\mathsf{MA} \\subseteq \\mathsf{QCMA} \\subseteq \\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq \\mathsf{PP} \\subseteq \\mathsf{PSPACE}</math>\n\nThe first inclusion follows from the definition of [[NP (complexity)|NP]]. The next two inclusions follow from the fact that the verifier is being made more powerful in each case. QCMA is contained in QMA since the verifier can force the prover to send a classical proof by measuring proofs as soon as they are received. The fact that QMA is contained in [[PP (complexity)|PP]] was shown by [[Alexei Kitaev]] and [[John Watrous (computer scientist)|John Watrous]]. PP is also easily shown to be in [[PSPACE]].\n\nIt is unknown if any of these inclusions is unconditionally strict, as it is not even known whether P is strictly contained in PSPACE or P = PSPACE. However, the currently best known upper bounds on QMA are\n<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Vyalyi\n| first = Mikhail N. \n| title = QMA = PP implies that PP contains PH \n| journal = Electronic Colloquium on Computational Complexity (ECCC)\n| year = 2003\n| url = https://eccc.weizmann.ac.il/eccc-reports/2003/TR03-021/index.html\n}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Gharibian\n| first = Sevag\n| last2 = Yirka\n| first2 = Justin \n| title = The complexity of simulating local measurements on quantum systems\n| journal = Quantum\n| year = 2019\n| volume = 3\n| page = 189\n| doi=10.22331/q-2019-09-30-189\n}}</ref>\n:<math>\\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> and <math>\\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math>,\nwhere both <math>\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> and <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math> are contained in <math>\\mathsf{PP}</math>. It is unlikely that <math>\\mathsf{QMA}</math> equals either <math>\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> or <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math>, as equality with the former would collapse the [[polynomial hierarchy|Polynomial-Time Hierarchy]] (PH), while equality with the latter would imply <math>\\mathsf{QMA}=\\mathsf{co}</math>-<math>\\mathsf{QMA}</math>. It is unknown whether  <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}\\subseteq\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> or vice versa.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.scottaaronson.com/democritus/lec13.html|title=PHYS771 Lecture 13: How Big are Quantum States?|last=Aaronson|first=Scott}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://groups.uni-paderborn.de/fg-qi/courses/UPB_QCOMPLEXITY/2019/notes/Lecture%205%20-%20Quantum%20Merlin%20Arthur%20(QMA)%20and%20strong%20error%20reduction.pdf|title=Lecture 5: Quantum Merlin Arthur (QMA) and strong error reduction|last=Gharibian|first=Sevag}}\n\n*{{CZoo|QMA|Q#qma}}\n\n{{quantum computing}}\n{{ComplexityClasses}}\n\n[[Category:Probabilistic complexity classes]]\n[[Category:Quantum complexity theory]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the mathematical theory|the coaxial RF connector|QMA and QN connector}}\n\nIn [[computational complexity theory]], '''QMA''', which stands for '''Quantum [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|Merlin Arthur]]''', is the quantum analog of the nonprobabilistic [[complexity class]] [[NP (complexity)|NP]] or the probabilistic complexity class [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|MA]]. It is related to [[BQP]] in the same way [[NP (complexity)|NP]] is related to [[P (complexity)|P]], or [[Arthur\u2013Merlin protocol|MA]] is related to [[Bounded-error probabilistic polynomial|BPP]].\n\nInformally, it is the set of [[decision problem]]s for which, when the answer is YES, there is a polynomial-size quantum proof (a quantum state) which convinces a polynomial-time quantum verifier of the fact with high probability. Moreover, when the answer is NO, every polynomial-size quantum state is rejected by the verifier with high probability.\n\nMore precisely, the proofs have to be verifiable in [[polynomial time]] on a [[quantum computer]], such that if the answer is indeed YES, the verifier accepts a correct proof with probability greater than 2/3, and if the answer is NO, then there is no proof which convinces the verifier to accept with probability greater than 1/3. As is usually the case, the constants 2/3 and 1/3 can be changed. Changing 2/3 to any constant strictly between 1/2 and 1, or changing 1/3 to any constant strictly between 0 and 1/2, does not change the class QMA.\n\n'''QAM''' is a related complexity class, in which fictional agents Arthur and Merlin carry out the sequence: Arthur generates a random string, Merlin answers with a quantum [[certificate (complexity)|certificate]] and Arthur verifies it as a BQP machine.\n\n== Definition ==\n\nA language L is in <math>\\mbox{QMA}(c,s)</math> if there exists a polynomial time quantum verifier V and a polynomial p(x) such that:<ref>{{cite arXiv|eprint=quant-ph/0210077v1|first1=Dorit|last1=Aharonov|author1-link= Dorit Aharonov|first2=Tomer|last2=Naveh|title=Quantum NP \u2013 A Survey|year=2002}}</ref><ref name=\"JW\">{{cite book|arxiv=0804.3401|first=John|last=Watrous|authorlink=John Watrous (computer scientist)|chapter=Quantum Computational Complexity|year=2009|title=Encyclopedia of Complexity and Systems Science|pages=7174\u20137201|doi=10.1007/978-0-387-30440-3_428|editor-first=Robert A.|editor-last=Meyers}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gharibian |first1=Sevag |last2=Huang |first2=Yichen |last3=Landau |first3=Zeph |last4=Shin |first4=Seung Woo |title=Quantum Hamiltonian Complexity |journal=Foundations and Trends in Theoretical Computer Science |date=2015 |volume=10 |issue=3 |pages=159\u2013282 |doi=10.1561/0400000066|arxiv=1401.3916 }}</ref>\n*<math>\\forall x \\in L</math>, there exists a quantum state <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math> such that the probability that V accepts the input <math>(|x\\rangle, |\\psi\\rangle)</math> is greater than <math>c</math>.\n*<math>\\forall x \\notin L</math>, for all quantum states <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math>, the probability that V accepts the input <math>(|x\\rangle, |\\psi\\rangle)</math> is less than <math>s</math>.\nwhere <math>|\\psi\\rangle</math> ranges over all quantum states with at most p(|x|) qubits.\n\nThe complexity class <math>\\mbox{QMA}</math> is defined to be equal to <math>\\mbox{QMA}({2}/{3},1/3)</math>. However, the constants are not too important since the class remains unchanged if <math>c</math> and <math>s</math> are set to any constants such that <math>c</math> is greater than <math>s</math>. Moreover, for any polynomials <math>q(n)</math> and <math>r(n)</math>, we have\n:<math>\\mbox{QMA}\\left(\\frac{2}{3},\\frac{1}{3}\\right) =\\mbox{QMA}\\left(\\frac{1}{2}+\\frac{1}{q(n)},\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{1}{q(n)}\\right)=\\mbox{QMA}(1-2^{-r(n)},2^{-r(n)})</math>.\n\n== Problems in QMA ==\n\nSince many interesting classes are contained in QMA, such as P, BQP and NP, all problems in those classes are also in QMA. However, there are problems that are in QMA but not known to be in NP or BQP. Some such well known problems are discussed below.\n\nA problem is said to be QMA-hard, analogous to [[NP-hard]], if every problem in QMA can be [[Reduction (complexity)|reduced]] to it. A problem is said to be QMA-[[complete (complexity)|complete]] if it is QMA-hard and in QMA.\n\n=== The local Hamiltonian problem ===\nThe local Hamiltonian problem is the quantum analogue of [[Maximum satisfiability problem|MAX-SAT]]. A Hamiltonian is a [[Hermitian matrix]] acting on quantum states, thus it is <math>2^n \\times 2^n</math> for a system of n [[qubit]]s. A k-local Hamiltonian is a Hamiltonian which can be written as the sum of Hamiltonians, each of which act non-trivially on at most k qubits (instead of all n qubits).\n\nThe k-local Hamiltonian problem, which is a [[promise problem]], is defined as follows. The input is a k-local Hamiltonian acting on n qubits, which is the sum of polynomially many Hermitian matrices that act on only k qubits. The input also contains two numbers <math>a< b \\in [0,1]</math>, such that <math>\\frac{1}{b-a}=O(n^c)</math> for some constant c. The problem is to determine whether the smallest eigenvalue of this Hamiltonian is less than <math>a</math> or greater than <math>b</math>, promised that one of these is the case.\n\nThe k-local Hamiltonian is QMA-complete for k \u2265 2.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Kempe | first1=Julia | author1-link = Julia Kempe | last2=Kitaev | first2=Alexei |author2-link= Alexei Kitaev | last3=Regev | first3=Oded | author3-link= Oded Regev | title=The complexity of the local Hamiltonian problem | year=2006 | journal=[[SIAM Journal on Computing]] | volume=35 | issue=5 | pages=1070\u20131097 | arxiv=quant-ph/0406180v2  | doi=10.1137/S0097539704445226}}.</ref>\n\nQMA-hardness results are known for even simplistic and physically realistic [[lattice models]] of [[qubits]] such as <ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Biamonte | first1=Jacob | last2=Love | first2=Peter | title=Realizable Hamiltonians for universal adiabatic quantum computers | journal=[[Physical Review A]] | year=2008 | volume=78 | issue=1 | pages=012352 | arxiv=0704.1287  | doi=10.1103/PhysRevA.78.012352 | bibcode=2008PhRvA..78a2352B}}.</ref>\n<math>\nH = \\sum_{i}h_i Z_i + \\sum_{i<j}J^{ij}Z_iZ_j + \\sum_{i<j}K^{ij}X_iX_j\n</math> \nwhere <math>Z, X</math> represent the [[Pauli matrices]] <math>\\sigma_z, \\sigma_x</math>.  Such models are applicable to universal [[adiabatic quantum computation]].\n\nThe Hamiltonians for the QMA-complete problem can also be restricted to act on a two dimensional grid of [[qubits]]<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Oliveira\n| first = Roberto\n|first2=Barbara M. | last2 = Terhal\n | title = The complexity of quantum spin systems on a two-dimensional square lattice\n| volume = 8\n| pages = 900\u2013924\n| journal = Quantum Information and Computation\n| year = 2008\n| issue = 10\n| arxiv = quant-ph/0504050\n| bibcode = 2005quant.ph..4050O\n}}</ref> or a line of quantum particles with 12 states per particle.<ref>{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1007/s00220-008-0710-3\n| volume = 287\n| issue = 1\n| pages = 41\u201365\n| last = Aharonov\n| first = Dorit | author1-link = Dorit Aharonov\n|first2=Daniel | last2 = Gottesman | author2-link = Daniel Gottesman |first3=Sandy | last3 = Irani |first4=Julia | last4= Kempe | author4-link = Julia Kempe\n | title = The power of quantum systems on a line\n| journal = [[Communications in Mathematical Physics]]\n| year = 2009 | bibcode=2009CMaPh.287...41A\n| arxiv= 0705.4077}}</ref>\n\n===Other QMA-complete problems===\nA list of known QMA-complete problems can be found at https://arxiv.org/abs/1212.6312.\n\n== Related classes ==\n\n'''QCMA''' (or '''MQA'''<ref name=\"JW\" />), which stands for Quantum Classical Merlin Arthur (or Merlin Quantum Arthur), is similar to QMA, but the proof has to be a classical string. It is not known whether QMA equals QCMA, although QCMA is clearly contained in QMA.\n\n'''QIP(k)''', which stands for [[Quantum Interactive Polynomial time]] (k messages), is a generalization of QMA where Merlin and Arthur can interact for k rounds. QMA is QIP(1). QIP(2) is known to be in PSPACE.<ref>{{Cite book | last1=Jain | first1=Rahul | last2=Upadhyay | first2=Sarvagya | last3=Watrous | first3=John | author3-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | title=[[Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science|Proceedings of the 50th Annual IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science (FOCS '09)]] | publisher=IEEE Computer Society | isbn=978-0-7695-3850-1 | year=2009 | chapter=Two-message quantum interactive proofs are in PSPACE | doi = 10.1109/FOCS.2009.30 | pages=534\u2013543}}</ref>\n\n'''[[QIP (complexity)|QIP]]''' is QIP(k) where k is allowed to be polynomial in the number of qubits. It is known that QIP(3) = QIP.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1=Watrous | first1=John | author1-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | title=PSPACE has constant-round quantum interactive proof systems | year=2003 | journal=[[Theoretical Computer Science (journal)|Theoretical Computer Science]] | volume=292 | issue=3 | pages=575\u2013588 | doi=10.1016/S0304-3975(01)00375-9 }}</ref> It is also known that QIP = [[IP (complexity)|IP]] = [[PSPACE]].<ref>{{cite journal | last1=Jain | first1=Rahul | last2=Ji | first2=Zhengfeng | last3=Upadhyay | first3=Sarvagya | last4=Watrous | first4=John | author4-link=John Watrous (computer scientist) | journal = [[Journal of the ACM]] | year=2011 | title=QIP = PSPACE | volume = 58 | issue = 6 | page = A30 | doi = 10.1145/2049697.2049704}}\n</ref>\n\n== Relationship to other classes ==\n\nQMA is related to other known [[complexity classes]] by the following relations:\n:<math>\\mathsf{P} \\subseteq \\mathsf{NP} \\subseteq \\mathsf{MA} \\subseteq \\mathsf{QCMA} \\subseteq \\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq \\mathsf{PP} \\subseteq \\mathsf{PSPACE}</math>\n\nThe first inclusion follows from the definition of [[NP (complexity)|NP]]. The next two inclusions follow from the fact that the verifier is being made more powerful in each case. QCMA is contained in QMA since the verifier can force the prover to send a classical proof by measuring proofs as soon as they are received. The fact that QMA is contained in [[PP (complexity)|PP]] was shown by [[Alexei Kitaev]] and [[John Watrous (computer scientist)|John Watrous]]. PP is also easily shown to be in [[PSPACE]].\n\nIt is unknown if any of these inclusions is unconditionally strict, as it is not even known whether P is strictly contained in PSPACE or P = PSPACE. However, the currently best known upper bounds on QMA are\n<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Vyalyi\n| first = Mikhail N. \n| title = QMA = PP implies that PP contains PH \n| journal = Electronic Colloquium on Computational Complexity (ECCC)\n| year = 2003\n| url = https://eccc.weizmann.ac.il/eccc-reports/2003/TR03-021/index.html\n}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal\n| last = Gharibian\n| first = Sevag\n| last2 = Yirka\n| first2 = Justin \n| title = The complexity of simulating local measurements on quantum systems\n| journal = Quantum\n| year = 2019\n| volume = 3\n| page = 189\n| doi=10.22331/q-2019-09-30-189\n}}</ref>\n:<math>\\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> and <math>\\mathsf{QMA}\\subseteq\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math>,\nwhere both <math>\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> and <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math> are contained in <math>\\mathsf{PP}</math>. It is unlikely that <math>\\mathsf{QMA}</math> equals either <math>\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> or <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}</math>, as equality with the former would collapse the [[polynomial hierarchy|Polynomial-Time Hierarchy]] (PH), while equality with the latter would imply <math>\\mathsf{QMA}=\\mathsf{co}</math>-<math>\\mathsf{QMA}</math>. It is unknown whether  <math>\\mathsf{P^{QMA[log]}}\\subseteq\\mathsf{A_0PP}</math> or vice versa.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.scottaaronson.com/democritus/lec13.html|title=PHYS771 Lecture 13: How Big are Quantum States?|last=Aaronson|first=Scott}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://groups.uni-paderborn.de/fg-qi/courses/UPB_QCOMPLEXITY/2019/notes/Lecture%205%20-%20Quantum%20Merlin%20Arthur%20(QMA)%20and%20strong%20error%20reduction.pdf|title=Lecture 5: Quantum Merlin Arthur (QMA) and strong error reduction|last=Gharibian|first=Sevag}}\n\n*{{CZoo|QMA|Q#qma}}\n\n{{quantum computing}}\n{{ComplexityClasses}}\n\n[[Category:Probabilistic complexity classes]]\n[[Category:Quantum complexity theory]]\n", "name_user": "Jaydavidmartin", "label": "safe", "comment": "grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QMA"}
{"title_page": "Kannada cinema", "text_new": "{{short description|Films in Kannada language}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox cinema market\n| name                 = Kannada cinema\n| image                = PVR cinema bangalore.jpg\n| image_size           = 180px\n| alt                  =\n| caption              = PVR cinemas In [[Bengaluru]]\n| screens              = 650 Single-screens in [[Karnataka]] \n| screens_per_capita   =\n| distributors         = \n* Vajreshwari Combines\n* Eshwari Productions\n*[[Chamundeshwari Studios]]\n*[[Jayanna Combines]]\n*[[Rockline Entertainments]]\n*[[Paramvah Studios]]\n*[[Pushkar Films]]\n*[[Lokesh Productions]]\n*[[Felis Creations]]\n*PRK Production\n*Thoogudeepa Productions\n*[[Hombale Films]]\n*Vrushbhadri Productions\n*[[Paramvah Studios]]\n| produced_year        = \n| produced_ref         = \n| produced_total       = \n| produced_fictional   =\n| produced_animated    =\n| produced_documentary =\n| admissions_year      =\n| admissions_ref       =\n| admissions_total     =\n| admissions_per_capita =\n| admissions_national  =\n| box_office_year      = 2018 till September\n| box_office_ref       = <ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=The Digital March Media & Entertainment in South India|url=http://www2.deloitte.com/content/dam/Deloitte/in/Documents/technology-media-telecommunications/in-tmt-economic-contribution-of-motion-picture-and-television-industry-noexp.pdf|publisher=Deloitte|accessdate=July 2018}}</ref>\n| box_office_total     = \n| box_office_national  = \n}}\n{{Indian cinema}}\n'''Kannada cinema''', also known as '''Sandalwood''', is the segment of [[Indian cinema]]<ref name=\"deccanherald.com\">[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/slideshow-sandalwood-rechristened-1518654#top] Link referring rechristening of sandalwod as chandanavana at world kannada summit</ref> dedicated to the production of motion pictures in the [[Kannada language]] widely spoken in the state of [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite book |author=Shampa Banerjee, Anil Srivastava|title= One Hundred Indian Feature Films: An Annotated Filmography|origyear=1988|year= 1988|publisher= Taylor & Francis|isbn= 0-8240-9483-2}}</ref><ref>[http://www.deccanherald.com/content/124106/when-rained-films.html When it rained films]. Deccanherald.com. Retrieved on 2017-07-29.</ref><ref>[http://www.filmfed.org/singlescreen.html \"Statewise number of single screens\"]. chitraloka.com (1913-05-03). Retrieved on 2013-07-29.</ref> The 1934 film ''[[Sati Sulochana]]'' directed by [[Yaragudipati Varada Rao|Y. V. Rao]] was the first talkie film in the Kannada language.<ref name=\"Rediff\">[http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/apr/13ms.htm Dr.Raj's impact on Kannada cinema] [[Rediff.com]]</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=First film to talk in Kannada  |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm |date=31 December 2004 |work=[[The Hindu]] |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=A revolutionary filmmaker  |url= http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/08/22/stories/2003082201400400.htm|date= 22 August 2003|work=[[The Hindu]]|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> It was also the first film starring [[Subbaiah Naidu]], and was the first motion picture screened in the erstwhile [[Mysore Kingdom]].<ref name=\"ss\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm|title=First film to talk in Kannada|work=Online Edition of the Hindu, dated 31 December 2004|accessdate=21 April 2007|location=Chennai, India|date=31 December 2004}}</ref> The film was produced by [[Chamanlal Doongaji]], who in 1932 founded ''South India Movietone'' in [[Bengaluru]].<ref name=thehindu>{{cite news |last1=Khajane |first1=Muralidhara |title=Philatelic show to mark 78th anniversary of \u2018Sati Sulochana' |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/philatelic-show-to-mark-78th-anniversary-of-sati-sulochana/article2929333.ece/amp/ |accessdate=3 September 2018 |work=The Hindu |date=25 February 2012 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref name=dailyhunt>{{cite news |title=Wealth of material found on first Kannada talkie - Deccan Herald {{!}} DailyHunt |url=https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/bangladesh/english/deccan+herald-epaper-deccan/wealth+of+material+found+on+first+kannada+talkie-newsid-85780599 |accessdate=3 September 2018 |work=DailyHunt |language=en}}</ref>\n\nMajor literary works have been adapted to the Kannada screen such as [[B. V. Karanth]]'s ''[[Chomana Dudi]]'' (1975), [[Girish Karnad]]'s ''[[Kaadu (1973 Kannada film)|Kaadu]]'' (1973), [[Pattabhirama Reddy Tikkavarapu|Pattabhirama Reddy]]'s ''[[Samskara (film)|Samskara]]'' (1970) (based on a novel by [[U. R. Ananthamurthy]]), which won the Bronze Leopard at [[Locarno International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://1nellore.com/1849/tikkavarapu-pattabhirama-reddy-poet-film-maker-of-international-fame/|title=Tikkavarapu Pattabhirama Reddy \u2013 Poet, Film maker of international fame from Nellore - 1Nellore.com|publisher=|access-date=26 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006102018/http://1nellore.com/1849/tikkavarapu-pattabhirama-reddy-poet-film-maker-of-international-fame/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and [[T. S. Nagabharana]]'s [[Mysore Mallige (film)|Mysuru Mallige]] (based on the works of acclaimed poet [[K. S. Narasimhaswamy]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bharatmovies.com/director/ts-nagabharana-movies.htm|title=TS Nagabharana movies list|website=www.bharatmovies.com|access-date=2016-11-04}}</ref>\n\nKannada cinema is known for producing experimental works such as [[Girish Kasaravalli]]'s ''[[Ghatashraddha]]'' (1977), which won the Ducats Award at the Manneham Film Festival Germany,<ref>{{cite web |title= Asiatic Film Mediale |url= http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/2002/uk/intro.html |publisher= asiaticafilmmediale.it|url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081116041627/http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/2002/uk/intro.html |archivedate= 16 November 2008 |df= dmy-all }}</ref> ''[[Dweepa]]'' (2002), which won Best Film at [[Moscow International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web |title= Girish Kasaravalli to be felicitated |url= http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/girish-kasaravalli-to-be-felicitated/article1765035.ece |publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date= 25 April 2011 |accessdate= 25 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"awa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/fline/fl1920/stories/20021011005912100.htm|title=A genius of theatre|work=The Frontline|date=12\u201325 October 2002|accessdate=2009-03-14}}</ref> [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]'s silent film ''[[Pushpaka Vimana (1987 film)|Pushpaka Vimana]]'' (1987), screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s docudrama  ''[[Killing Veerappan]]'' (2016), and [[Prashanth Neel]]'s [[Historical drama]], ''[[K.G.F: Chapter 1]]'' (2018),<ref name=\"Oscar nominees among 240 films to be screened during Biffes\">{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Oscar-nominees-among-240-films-to-be-screened-during-Biffes/article17104930.ece | title=Oscar nominees among 240 films to be screened during Biffes | publisher=The Hindu | accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Killing-Veerappan-is-a-Slick-RGV-Thriller/2016/01/02/article3206836.ece|title=Killing Veerappan is a Slick RGV Thriller|work=The New Indian Express}}</ref> which became the first Kannada language film to have grossed \u20b9250 crores worldwide at the box office.<ref>{{cite|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190113152018/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/kgf-becomes-first-kannada-film-to-break-into-rs-200-cr-club-njan-prakashan-declared-blockbuster-5862501.html/amp|title=KGF becomes first Kannada film to break into Rs 200 cr club; Njan Prakashan declared blockbuster|date=2019-01-09|archivedate=2018-01-13|work=Firstpost}}</ref>\n\n==Early history==\n[[File:Honnappa Bhagavathar 1948.jpg|thumb|150px|upright|right|Kannada film doyen [[Honnappa Bhagavathar]]]]\n[[File:Rajkumar 2009 stamp of India.jpg|thumb|150px|upright|right|[[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] on a 2009 stamp in India]]\nIn 1934, the first Kannada [[talkie]], ''[[Sati Sulochana]]'',<ref>[http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm \"First film to talk in Kannada\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070105012711/http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm |date=5 January 2007 }} article in ''The Hindu''</ref> appeared in theatres, followed by ''[[Bhakta Dhruva]]'' (aka ''Dhruva Kumar''). ''Sati Sulochana'' was shot in [[Kolhapur]] at the Chatrapathi studio; most filming, sound recording, and post-production was done in [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"Routledge\">{{cite book|author1=K. Moti Gokulsing|author2=Wimal Dissanayake|title=Routledge Handbook of Indian Cinemas|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=djUFmlFbzFkC|date=17 April 2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-136-77284-9}}</ref>\n\nIn 1949, [[Honnappa Bhagavathar]], who had earlier acted in Gubbi Veeranna's films, produced ''[[Bhakta Kumbara]]'' and starred in the lead role along with [[Pandaribai]]. In 1955, Bhagavathar again produced a Kannada film, ''[[Mahakavi Kalidasa]]'', in which he introduced actress [[B. Saroja Devi]].<ref name=\"Routledge\"/> [[B. S. Ranga]] was an Indian photographer, actor, producer and director made many landmark movies in [[Kannada]], under Vikram Studios.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/ratnapuri-ilavarasi-1960/article6229101.ece\n|title=Ratnapuri Ilavarasi (1960)|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=19 July 2014|accessdate=5 April 2018|last=Guy|first=Randor|authorlink=Randor Guy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731094156/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/ratnapuri-ilavarasi-1960/article6229101.ece|url-status=live\n| archivedate=31 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Mainstream==\n[[Matinee idol]], [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] entered Kannada cinema after his long stint as a dramatist with [[Gubbi Veeranna]]'s ''Gubbi Drama Company'', which he joined at the age of eight, before he got his first break as a lead in the 1954 film ''[[Bedara Kannappa]]''.<ref name=\"Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema\">{{cite web|title=Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/rajobit/20060412.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|accessdate=24 April 2017|date=12 April 2006}}</ref>\n\nHe went on to essay a variety of roles and excelling in portraying mythological and historical characters in films such as ''[[Bhakta Kanakadasa]]'' (1960), ''[[Ranadheera Kanteerava]]'' (1960), ''[[Satya Harishchandra (1965 Kannada film)|Satya Harishchandra]]'' (1965), ''[[Immadi Pulikeshi (film)|Immadi Pulikeshi]]'' (1967), ''[[Sri Krishnadevaraya (film)|Sri Krishnadevaraya]]'' (1970), ''[[Bhakta Kumbara]]'' (1974), ''[[Mayura (film)|Mayura]]'' (1975), ''[[Babruvahana (film)|Babruvahana]]'' (1977) and ''[[Bhakta Prahlada (1983 film)|Bhakta Prahlada]]'' (1983). His wife [[Parvathamma Rajkumar]] founded Film production and distribution company, Vajreshwari Combines.<ref name=\"Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema\"/>\n\nMethod actor [[Shankar Nag]] received the inaugural [[IFFI Best Actor Award (Male)]]: Silver Peacock Award\" at the [[7th International Film Festival of India]] for his work in the film ''[[Ondanondu Kaladalli]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EKo-DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT157&lpg=PT157&dq=iffi+girish+karnad+1979&source=bl&ots=i-oQyInjhS&sig=ouE2Erj4qaPNVQsqJMuI8UEP7Mc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjwpca06c_YAhUjSo8KHRMmBgIQ6AEIUTAJ#v=onepage&q=iffi+girish+karnad+1979&f=false|title=Conscience of The Race|first=BIBEKANANDA|last=RAY|date=5 April 2017|publisher=Publications Division Ministry of Information & Broadcasting|via=Google Books}}</ref> He is the younger brother of actor [[Anant Nag]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-14/news-interviews/37712791_1_shankar-nag-documentary-auto-raja|title=This one's for Shankar Nag - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YbG4HPNDlsk|title=Shankar Nag Last Interview - Part 2|first=|last=Anand Chandrashekar|date=7 November 2009|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> [[M. V. Vasudeva Rao]] was starred in over 200 films in his career; however, post ''[[Chomana Dudi]]'', he only played minor roles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rao|first1=M. K. Bhaskar|title=A natural|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/apr13/at3.htm|website=Deccan Herald|accessdate=2 May 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020425090527/http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/apr13/at3.htm|archivedate=25 April 2002|date=14 April 2002}}</ref>\n\n[[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] entered Kannada cinema with the National Award-winning movie ''[[Vamshavruksha]]'' (1972) directed by [[Girish Karnad]] based on the novel written by [[S. L. Bhyrappa]]. His first lead role was in ''[[Naagarahaavu]]'', directed by [[Puttanna Kanagal]] and based on a novel by [[T. R. Subba Rao]]. It was the first in Kannada film history to complete 100 days in three main theatres of Bangalore. In his 37-year career, he has played a variety of roles in more than 200 films.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishnuvardhan-helped-me-to-get-stardom-rajinikanth/article76796.ece | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Vishnuvardhan helped me to get stardom: Rajinikanth | date=7 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nWith his debut in [[Puttanna Kanagal]]'s National Award-winning Kannada film ''[[Naagarahaavu]]'' (1972), [[Ambareesh]]'s acting career commenced with a brief phase of portraying antagonistic and supporting characters. After establishing himself as a lead actor portraying rebellious characters on screen in a number of commercially successful films, he earned the moniker \"rebel star\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/174720/when-rebel-star-rewinds-past.html|title=When 'Rebel Star' rewinds past days in Mysore|newspaper=Deccan Herald|date=20 September 2014}}</ref> He also earned the nickname ''Mandyada Gandu'' (English: Man of [[Mandya]])<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/mandyada-gandu-gets-rousing-welcome/article5907186.ece|title=\u2018Mandyada Gandu\u2019 gets rousing welcome|newspaper=The Hindu|date=13 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[B. Saroja Devi]] is One of the most successful female leads in the history of Indian cinema, she acted in around 200 films in over six decades.<ref>[http://www.chitramala.com/articles/saroja-devi-4189.html Documentary on legendary Saroja Devi - Chitramala.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711020420/http://www.chitramala.com/articles/saroja-devi-4189.html |date=11 July 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"ToI_greatest_2013\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/B-Saroja-Devi-in-the-list-of-greatest-Indianactresses-ever/articleshow/19895895.cms |title=B Saroja Devi in the list of greatest Indian actresses ever |author=Taniya Talukdar |date=5 May 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India }}</ref> She is known by the epithets \"''Abinaya Saraswathi''\" ([[Saraswati|Saraswathi]] of acting) in Kannada and \"''Kannadathu Paingili''\" (Kannada's Parrot) in Tamil.<ref name=\"ToI_greatest_2013\"/>\n\n==Neo-realistic Cinema==\n{{main|Parallel cinema}}\nKannada Cinema majorly contributed to the [[Parallel cinema]] movement of India.<ref name=\"Kasaravalli\">{{cite|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/parallel-cinema-girish-kasaravalli-look-kannada-industrys-stalwart-filmmaker-72172|title=The parallel cinema of Girish Kasaravalli: A look at Kannada industry's stalwart filmmaker|date=2017-11-07|work=The News Minute}}</ref> Directors like [[Girish Kasaravalli]],<ref name=\"Kasaravalli\"/> [[Girish Karnad]],<ref name=\"Karnad\">{{cite|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/kannadas-parallel-cinema-loses-its-star/article26662943.ece|title=Kannada's parallel cinema loses its star|date=2019-03-28|work=The Hindu}}</ref> [[G. V. Iyer]]<ref name=\"Karnad\"/> were the early names to join the movement. [[T. S. Nagabharana]]<ref>{{cite book |date=2003 |title=Cinema in India, Volume 3 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WQtlAAAAMAAJ&q=Puttanna+Kanagal&dq=Puttanna+Kanagal&hl=en&sa=X&ei=uqSgVfWxG5PSoATz-p6QBg&ved=0CDoQ6AEwBzge |publisher=Mangala Chandran |access-date=July 11, 2015}}</ref> and [[BV Karanth]] were also popular names in the movement. [[Puttanna Kanagal]]'s films were however considered as a bridge between the Mainstream and the Parallel Cinema.\n\n==Modern Era==\n[[Prakash Raj]] began his acting career with [[Doordarshan]] serials such as ''Bisilu Kudure'' (Kannada) and ''[[Guddada Bhootha]]'' ([[Tulu language|Tulu]] and Kannada).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/if-artistes-become-cowards-they-make-society-a-coward-prakash-raj-4975924/lite|title=If artistes become cowards, they make society a coward: Prakash Raj}}</ref> He later took up supporting roles in [[Kannada language|Kannada]] films such as ''Ramachari'', ''[[Ranadheera]]'', ''[[Nishkarsha]]'' and ''[[Lockup Death]]''. He was noticed for his dialogue delivery and histrionics. His breakthrough role came in ''[[Harakeya Kuri]]'', directed by [[K. S. L. Swamy]] starring Vishnuvardhan, with whom he had acted in other films such as ''[[Mithileya Seetheyaru]]'', ''[[Muthina Haara]]'' and ''[[Nishkarsha]]''. Prakash re-entered Kannada films through ''[[Nagamandala]]'' in 1997, directed by [[T. S. Nagabharana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/india/prakash-raj-exclusive-everyone-has-the-right-to-differ-but-this-is-orchestrated-trolling-and-you-cannot-threaten-me-with-continuous-abuse-4174937.html/amp|title=Prakash Raj exclusive: Everyone has the right to differ, but this is orchestrated trolling. And you cannot threaten me with continuous abuse}}</ref> Veteran Kannada actor [[Shakti Prasad]]'s son [[Arjun Sarja]] is known for his works in South Indian cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/41510/sandalwood/four-films-announced-for-23rd-march-news-details |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320165539/http://www.supergoodmovies.com/41510/sandalwood/four-films-announced-for-23rd-march-news-details |archivedate=20 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was starred in works such as [[Prasad (2012 film)|Prasad]], the film was screened at the [[Berlin Film Festival]], and Arjun received the Karnataka State Award for his performance.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-23/news-interviews/31090458_1_martin-gropius-bau-festival-director-indian-film]</ref>\n\n[[Sanchari Vijay]]'s portrayal of a transgender won him the [[National Film Award for Best Actor|National Best Actor Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vijay bags National Award for Best Actor|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Vijay-bags-National-Award-for-Best-Actor/articleshow/46676471.cms|publisher=timesofindia|date=24 March 2015|accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sanchari Vijay Actor\u2013Profile and biography|url=http://cinetrooth.in/2015/06/21/sanchari-vijay-actor-profile-and-biography/|publisher=cinetrooth|date=21 June 2015|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Vijay elated on winning best actor award|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/467499/vijay-elated-winning-actor-award.html|publisher=deccanherald|date=25 March 2015|accessdate=2015-03-26}}</ref> With the award win, Vijay became the third actor after [[M. V. Vasudeva Rao]], and [[Charuhasan]] to win the National Award for Best Actor for performing in a [[Kannada film]].<ref>http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/meet-the-first-kannada-actor-to-win-a-national-award-south/20150325.htm</ref>\n\n[[Shiva Rajkumar]] is known for his work in ''[[Janumada Jodi]]'', ''[[Anand (1986 film)|Anand]]'', ''[[Ratha Sapthami]]'', ''[[Nammoora Mandara Hoove]]'', ''[[Om]]'' ''[[Simhada Mari]]'', and ''[[Chigurida Kanasu]]''. He acted in ''[[Sugreeva (film)|Sugreeva]]'', which was shot in 18 hours. His ''[[Om (Kannada film)|Om]]'', directed by [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]], set a trend of gangster movies in [[Kannada]] and other film industries in India. It continues to be shown even to this day.<ref>[http://kannada.oneindia.in/movies/news/2010/09/01-upendra-om-re-release-on-sept-3.html \u0caa\u0ccd\u0cb0\u0cc7\u0c95\u0ccd\u0cb7\u0c95\u0cb0 \u0c92\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cbe\u0caf\u0ca6 \u0cae\u0cc7\u0cb0\u0cc6\u0c97\u0cc6 \u0cae\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cc6 \u0cac\u0c82\u0ca6\u0cbf\u0ca6\u0cc6 \u0c93\u0c82!], One India, 1 September 2010</ref>\n\n[[Rockline Venkatesh]] founded [[Rockline Entertainments]] which has produced over twenty five films as of 2012.<ref name=\"63rdaward\">{{cite press_release|title=63rd National Film Awards|url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf|format=PDF|publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]]|date=28 March 2016|accessdate=28 March 2016}}</ref> New age actors [[Puneeth Rajkumar]], [[Rakshith Shetty]], and [[Yash (actor)|Yash]] are one of the highest-paid actors in Sandalwood.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-pk-mr-mrs-ramachari-dominate-bengaluru-collection-centres-619818 Box Office Collection: 'PK', 'Mr & Mrs Ramachari' Dominate Bengaluru Collection Centres]. Ibtimes.co.in (9 January 2015). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/birthday-gift-to-yash-ramachari-to-enter-20-cr-club-soon-news-kannada-pbikMujcjecag.html|title=Birthday gift to Yash: Ramachari to enter cr club soon!|agency=www.sify.com|access-date=22 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822145507/https://www.sify.com/movies/birthday-gift-to-yash-ramachari-to-enter-20-cr-club-soon-news-kannada-pbikMujcjecag.html|archive-date=22 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= 'Mr and Mrs Ramachari' Review: Audience Live Response |url= http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mr-mrs-ramachari-review-audience-live-response-618291 |publisher= ibtimes.co.in |date= 25 December 2014 |accessdate= 2 January 2015}}</ref> The [[Rakshith Shetty]] starrer ''[[Kirik Party]]'' opened to {{cn span|widespread acclaim from critics and audiences alike|date=January 2020}} and went on to become the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing film]] of the year by collecting \u20b950 [[crore]]<ref name=\"ittt\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party dubbed by malayalam movie premam and Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|publisher=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> against production budget \u20b94 crore,<ref name=\"th\">{{cite web|title=The budget of \u2018Kirik Party\u2019 would be around \u20b94crore|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/rakshith-shettys-kirik-party-to-go-on-the-floors-in-march/article8191273.ece\n|work=The Hindu}}</ref> and completed 150-days in main centers of [[Karnataka]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/krik-party-rakshit-shetty-rashmika-mandanna-celebrate-150-days-981176-2017-06-06|title=Kirik Party completes 150 days: Rakshit Shetty, Rashmika Mandanna celebrate with fans|website=India Today}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, [[K.G.F: Chapter 1]] became the first [[Kannada]] film to gross \u20b9100 crores, \u20b9200 crores and \u20b9250 crores at the box office. A sequel is slated to release on 23 October 2020.<ref>https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/yash-reveals-he-has-approached-sanjay-dutt-for-kgf-chapter-2-1452187-2019-02-09</ref>\n\n==Film Score==\nComposer [[Hamsalekha]] is usually referred to by the title ''Naadha Brahma'' (English: The [[Brahma]] of Music) who is considered to be the major cause for the change in the music composing and lyric writing style which would appeal much to the younger generation. He integrated folk and introduced western musical sensibilities into the Kannada cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chitraloka.com/news/1472-hamsalekha-60.html|title=Hamsalekha 60|publisher=Chitraloka|date=23 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/dr-hamsalekha-now-kannada-news-107448|title=Dr. Hamsalekha now|publisher=Indiaglitz|date=14 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[Mano Murthy]] scored the blockbuster film [[Mungaru Male]] starring [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]] and [[Pooja Gandhi]]. Upon the album's release, it topped the charts with the song \"[[Anisuthide]]\" receiving significant radio and TV air time.<ref name = hindu>{{cite news |title='Mungaru Male' still tops the charts |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/mungaru-male-still-tops-the-charts/article1843484.ece |newspaper=The Hindu |date=17 May 2014 |accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> The album emerged as a massive success topping every Kannada music chart. It was reported that by mid-May 2007, over 200,000 copies were sold in [[compact disc]]s.<ref>{{cite news |title='Mungaru Male' album a mega hit |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1273374021.html |accessdate=10 October 2015 |work=Hindustan Times |date=18 May 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151010052639/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1273374021.html |archivedate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Film Schools==\nThe first government institute in India to start technical courses related to films was established in 1941 named as occupational institute then called the Sri Jayachamarajendra (S J) Polytechnic in [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]]. In September 1996, two specialized courses, Cinematography and Sound & Television were separated and the [[Government Film and Television Institute]] was started at [[Hesaraghatta]], under the World Bank Assisted Project for Technician Development in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=GFTI|url=http://www.filminstitutebangalore.com/index.htm|website=www.filminstitutebangalore.com|accessdate=22 August 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140821235404/http://www.filminstitutebangalore.com/index.htm|archivedate=21 August 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==State Awards==\n[[File:Karnataka Chalanachitra Kalavidara Sangha-img.jpg|thumb|150px|right|Karnataka Chalanachitra Kalavidara Sangha in [[Chamrajpet|Chamrajapet]]]]\n* [[Karnataka State Film Awards]]\n* [[Udaya Film Awards]]\n* [[Suvarna Film Awards]]\n\n==State Festivals==\n* [[Bangalore International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biffes.in/|title=Bengaluru International Film Festival - BIFFES|work=Bengaluru International Film Festival}}</ref>\n\n==Other Awards==\n* [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n* [[SIIMA Awards]]\n* [[IIFA Utsavam]]\n* [[Mirchi Music Awards South]]\n* [[South Scope|South Scope Awards]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Kannada-language films]]\n* [[Media in Karnataka]]\n* [[Cinema of India]]\n* [[Media of India]]\n* [[List of Kannada film actresses]]\n\n==Highest-grossing Kannada films by year==\n{| style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Film\n! Year\n! Director(s)\n! Studio(s)\n! Worldwide gross\n! {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|- \n| 1 \n| ''[[K.G.F: Chapter 1]]'' \n| 2018\n| [[Prashanth Neel]]\n| Hombale Films\n| {{INRConvert|243|c}}\u2013{{INRConvert|250|c}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/amp/entertainment/box-office/article/yash-starrer-kgf-collects-rs-243-10-crore-at-the-worldwide-box-office-in-50-days-will-it-make-rs-250-crore/363115|title=Kannada Cinema's Pride! Yash starrer KGF collects Rs 243.10 crore at the worldwide box office in 50 days; will it make Rs 250 crore? &#124; Entertainment News|website=www.timesnownews.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/yash-reveals-he-has-approached-sanjay-dutt-for-kgf-chapter-2-1452187-2019-02-09\n|title=Yash's film KGF: Chapter 1 made Rs 250 crore at the box office worldwide and became a magnum-opus. Now, the makers are busy with pre-production work of KGF: Chapter 2.|date=2019-02-09|work=indiatoday}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Kurukshetra (2019 film)|Kurukshetra]]\n| 2019\n| [[Kurukshetra (2019 film)|Naganna]]\n| Vrushabhadri Productions\n| {{INRConvert|100|c}}\n|\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Pailwan]]\n| 2019\n| [[S. Krishna]]\n| RRR Motion Pictures\n| {{INRConvert|50|c}}\n|\n|-\n| 4\n|''[[Raajakumara]]''\n| 2017\n| [[Santhosh Ananddram]]\n| Hombale Productions\n| {{INRConvert|75|c}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsable.asianetnews.tv/entertainment/puneeth-rajkumar-sudeep-yash-darshan-salary-raajakumara-anjaniputra-kannada-stars-salary|title=This man is the highly paid actor in Kannada film industry|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|5\n| ''[[Mungaru Male]]''\n| 2006\n|[[Yogaraj Bhat]]\n| E. K. Entertainers\n| {{INRConvert|50|c}}\n|<ref name=\"TheHindu Mungaru 50 crore\">{{cite web|title=Stage set for Mungaru Male sequel|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/stage-set-for-mungaru-male-sequel/article6630772.ece|work=The Hindu|accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"TOI Mungaru 50 crore\">{{cite web|title=Ganesh all set for Mungaru Male 2|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Ganesh-all-set-for-Mungaru-Male-2/articleshow/46698706.cms|website=The Times of India|accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| 2016\n| [[Rishab Shetty]]\n| Paramvah Studios\n| {{INRConvert|50|c}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|website=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari]]''\n| 2014\n|[[Santhosh Ananddram]]\n| Jayanna Combines\n| {{INRConvert|50|c}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/content-over-star-power-story-of-south-cinema-in-first-half-of-2015/story-KaqHkEArfSnQWbN6iJ5dCI.html|title=Content over star power: Story of south cinema in first half of 2015|date=1 July 2015|work=[[Hindustan Times]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]''\n| 2019\n| [[Pon Kumaran]]\n| Media House Studio\n| {{INRConvert|50|c}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/entertainment/yajamana-grosses-rs-50-crore-becomes-darshan-s-first-movie-to-cross-the-mark-kgf-rajakumara-the-villain-pod1xd|title=Yajamana grosses Rs 50 crore, becomes Darshan's first movie to cross the mark|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd}}</ref>\n|- style=\"width:50px; border:1px solid #aaa;\" span\n| rowspan=\"3\"|6\n|''[[Doddmane Hudga]]''\n| 2016\n| [[Duniya Soori]]\n| Ajay Pictures\n| {{INRConvert|40|c}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/raajakumara-box-office-collection-puneeth-rajkumars-film-cashing-ugadi-holiday-721178|title=Dodmane Hudga lifetime collection is over \u20b940 crore|work=www.ibtimes.co.in}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Sangolli Rayanna (film)|Krantiveera Sangolli Rayanna]]''\n| 2012\n| [[Kurukshetra (2019 film)|Naganna]]\n| Sri Sangolli Rayanna Cine Combines\n| {{INRConvert|40|c}}\n|<ref name=\"TOISangolliRayanna\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Sangolli-Rayanna-set-to-complete-100-days/articleshow/18239373.cms|title=Sangolli Rayanna set to complete 100 days|work=The Times of India|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Uppi 2]]''\n| 2015\n| [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]]\n| Upendra Productions\n| {{INRConvert|40|c}}\n|<ref>{{cite news|author=A Sharadhaa |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bengaluru/Sandalwood-hits-Rangitaranga-and-Uppi-2-Run-to-Full-House-in-USA/2015/08/17/article2977653.ece |title=Sandalwood hits Rangitaranga and Uppi 2 Run to Full House in USA |newspaper=The New Indian Express |date=17 August 2015 |accessdate=24 August 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{National Film Award Best Feature Film Kannada}}\n{{Cinema of Karnataka|state=collapsed}}\n{{Cinema of India}}\n{{Media of India}}\n{{Worldcinema}}\n{{Karnataka topics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cinema Of Karnataka}}\n[[Category:Cinema of Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Kannada cinema]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Films in Kannada language}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox cinema market\n| name                 = Kannada cinema\n| image                = PVR cinema bangalore.jpg\n| image_size           = 180px\n| alt                  =\n| caption              = PVR cinemas In [[Bengaluru]]\n| screens              = 650 Single-screens in [[Karnataka]] \n| screens_per_capita   =\n| distributors         = \n* Vajreshwari Combines\n* Eshwari Productions\n*[[Chamundeshwari Studios]]\n*[[Jayanna Combines]]\n*[[Rockline Entertainments]]\n*[[Paramvah Studios]]\n*[[Pushkar Films]]\n*[[Lokesh Productions]]\n*[[Felis Creations]]\n*PRK Production\n*Thoogudeepa Productions\n*[[Hombale Films]]\n*Vrushbhadri Productions\n*[[Paramvah Studios]]\n| produced_year        = \n| produced_ref         = \n| produced_total       = \n| produced_fictional   =\n| produced_animated    =\n| produced_documentary =\n| admissions_year      =\n| admissions_ref       =\n| admissions_total     =\n| admissions_per_capita =\n| admissions_national  =\n| box_office_year      = 2018 till September\n| box_office_ref       = <ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=The Digital March Media & Entertainment in South India|url=http://www2.deloitte.com/content/dam/Deloitte/in/Documents/technology-media-telecommunications/in-tmt-economic-contribution-of-motion-picture-and-television-industry-noexp.pdf|publisher=Deloitte|accessdate=July 2018}}</ref>\n| box_office_total     = \n| box_office_national  = \n}}\n{{Indian cinema}}\n'''Kannada cinema''', also known as '''Sandalwood''', is the segment of [[Indian cinema]]<ref name=\"deccanherald.com\">[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/slideshow-sandalwood-rechristened-1518654#top] Link referring rechristening of sandalwod as chandanavana at world kannada summit</ref> dedicated to the production of motion pictures in the [[Kannada language]] widely spoken in the state of [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite book |author=Shampa Banerjee, Anil Srivastava|title= One Hundred Indian Feature Films: An Annotated Filmography|origyear=1988|year= 1988|publisher= Taylor & Francis|isbn= 0-8240-9483-2}}</ref><ref>[http://www.deccanherald.com/content/124106/when-rained-films.html When it rained films]. Deccanherald.com. Retrieved on 2017-07-29.</ref><ref>[http://www.filmfed.org/singlescreen.html \"Statewise number of single screens\"]. chitraloka.com (1913-05-03). Retrieved on 2013-07-29.</ref> The 1934 film ''[[Sati Sulochana]]'' directed by [[Yaragudipati Varada Rao|Y. V. Rao]] was the first talkie film in the Kannada language.<ref name=\"Rediff\">[http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/apr/13ms.htm Dr.Raj's impact on Kannada cinema] [[Rediff.com]]</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=First film to talk in Kannada  |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm |date=31 December 2004 |work=[[The Hindu]] |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=A revolutionary filmmaker  |url= http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/08/22/stories/2003082201400400.htm|date= 22 August 2003|work=[[The Hindu]]|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> It was also the first film starring [[Subbaiah Naidu]], and was the first motion picture screened in the erstwhile [[Mysore Kingdom]].<ref name=\"ss\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm|title=First film to talk in Kannada|work=Online Edition of the Hindu, dated 31 December 2004|accessdate=21 April 2007|location=Chennai, India|date=31 December 2004}}</ref> The film was produced by [[Chamanlal Doongaji]], who in 1932 founded ''South India Movietone'' in [[Bengaluru]].<ref name=thehindu>{{cite news |last1=Khajane |first1=Muralidhara |title=Philatelic show to mark 78th anniversary of \u2018Sati Sulochana' |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/philatelic-show-to-mark-78th-anniversary-of-sati-sulochana/article2929333.ece/amp/ |accessdate=3 September 2018 |work=The Hindu |date=25 February 2012 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref name=dailyhunt>{{cite news |title=Wealth of material found on first Kannada talkie - Deccan Herald {{!}} DailyHunt |url=https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/bangladesh/english/deccan+herald-epaper-deccan/wealth+of+material+found+on+first+kannada+talkie-newsid-85780599 |accessdate=3 September 2018 |work=DailyHunt |language=en}}</ref>\n\nMajor literary works have been adapted to the Kannada screen such as [[B. V. Karanth]]'s ''[[Chomana Dudi]]'' (1975), [[Girish Karnad]]'s ''[[Kaadu (1973 Kannada film)|Kaadu]]'' (1973), [[Pattabhirama Reddy Tikkavarapu|Pattabhirama Reddy]]'s ''[[Samskara (film)|Samskara]]'' (1970) (based on a novel by [[U. R. Ananthamurthy]]), which won the Bronze Leopard at [[Locarno International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://1nellore.com/1849/tikkavarapu-pattabhirama-reddy-poet-film-maker-of-international-fame/|title=Tikkavarapu Pattabhirama Reddy \u2013 Poet, Film maker of international fame from Nellore - 1Nellore.com|publisher=|access-date=26 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006102018/http://1nellore.com/1849/tikkavarapu-pattabhirama-reddy-poet-film-maker-of-international-fame/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and [[T. S. Nagabharana]]'s [[Mysore Mallige (film)|Mysuru Mallige]] (based on the works of acclaimed poet [[K. S. Narasimhaswamy]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bharatmovies.com/director/ts-nagabharana-movies.htm|title=TS Nagabharana movies list|website=www.bharatmovies.com|access-date=2016-11-04}}</ref>\n\nKannada cinema is known for producing experimental works such as [[Girish Kasaravalli]]'s ''[[Ghatashraddha]]'' (1977), which won the Ducats Award at the Manneham Film Festival Germany,<ref>{{cite web |title= Asiatic Film Mediale |url= http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/2002/uk/intro.html |publisher= asiaticafilmmediale.it|url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081116041627/http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/2002/uk/intro.html |archivedate= 16 November 2008 |df= dmy-all }}</ref> ''[[Dweepa]]'' (2002), which won Best Film at [[Moscow International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web |title= Girish Kasaravalli to be felicitated |url= http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/girish-kasaravalli-to-be-felicitated/article1765035.ece |publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date= 25 April 2011 |accessdate= 25 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"awa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/fline/fl1920/stories/20021011005912100.htm|title=A genius of theatre|work=The Frontline|date=12\u201325 October 2002|accessdate=2009-03-14}}</ref> [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]'s silent film ''[[Pushpaka Vimana (1987 film)|Pushpaka Vimana]]'' (1987), screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s docudrama  ''[[Killing Veerappan]]'' (2016), and [[Prashanth Neel]]'s [[Historical drama]], ''[[K.G.F: Chapter 1]]'' (2018),<ref name=\"Oscar nominees among 240 films to be screened during Biffes\">{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Oscar-nominees-among-240-films-to-be-screened-during-Biffes/article17104930.ece | title=Oscar nominees among 240 films to be screened during Biffes | publisher=The Hindu | accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Killing-Veerappan-is-a-Slick-RGV-Thriller/2016/01/02/article3206836.ece|title=Killing Veerappan is a Slick RGV Thriller|work=The New Indian Express}}</ref> which became the first Kannada language film to have grossed \u20b9250 crores worldwide at the box office.<ref>{{cite|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190113152018/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/kgf-becomes-first-kannada-film-to-break-into-rs-200-cr-club-njan-prakashan-declared-blockbuster-5862501.html/amp|title=KGF becomes first Kannada film to break into Rs 200 cr club; Njan Prakashan declared blockbuster|date=2019-01-09|archivedate=2018-01-13|work=Firstpost}}</ref>\n\n==Early history==\n[[File:Honnappa Bhagavathar 1948.jpg|thumb|150px|upright|right|Kannada film doyen [[Honnappa Bhagavathar]]]]\n[[File:Rajkumar 2009 stamp of India.jpg|thumb|150px|upright|right|[[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] on a 2009 stamp in India]]\nIn 1934, the first Kannada [[talkie]], ''[[Sati Sulochana]]'',<ref>[http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm \"First film to talk in Kannada\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070105012711/http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2004/12/31/stories/2004123102420300.htm |date=5 January 2007 }} article in ''The Hindu''</ref> appeared in theatres, followed by ''[[Bhakta Dhruva]]'' (aka ''Dhruva Kumar''). ''Sati Sulochana'' was shot in [[Kolhapur]] at the Chatrapathi studio; most filming, sound recording, and post-production was done in [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"Routledge\">{{cite book|author1=K. Moti Gokulsing|author2=Wimal Dissanayake|title=Routledge Handbook of Indian Cinemas|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=djUFmlFbzFkC|date=17 April 2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-136-77284-9}}</ref>\n\nIn 1949, [[Honnappa Bhagavathar]], who had earlier acted in Gubbi Veeranna's films, produced ''[[Bhakta Kumbara]]'' and starred in the lead role along with [[Pandaribai]]. In 1955, Bhagavathar again produced a Kannada film, ''[[Mahakavi Kalidasa]]'', in which he introduced actress [[B. Saroja Devi]].<ref name=\"Routledge\"/> [[B. S. Ranga]] was an Indian photographer, actor, producer and director made many landmark movies in [[Kannada]], under Vikram Studios.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/ratnapuri-ilavarasi-1960/article6229101.ece\n|title=Ratnapuri Ilavarasi (1960)|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=19 July 2014|accessdate=5 April 2018|last=Guy|first=Randor|authorlink=Randor Guy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731094156/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/ratnapuri-ilavarasi-1960/article6229101.ece|url-status=live\n| archivedate=31 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Mainstream==\n[[Matinee idol]], [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] entered Kannada cinema after his long stint as a dramatist with [[Gubbi Veeranna]]'s ''Gubbi Drama Company'', which he joined at the age of eight, before he got his first break as a lead in the 1954 film ''[[Bedara Kannappa]]''.<ref name=\"Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema\">{{cite web|title=Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/rajobit/20060412.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|accessdate=24 April 2017|date=12 April 2006}}</ref>\n\nHe went on to essay a variety of roles and excelling in portraying mythological and historical characters in films such as ''[[Bhakta Kanakadasa]]'' (1960), ''[[Ranadheera Kanteerava]]'' (1960), ''[[Satya Harishchandra (1965 Kannada film)|Satya Harishchandra]]'' (1965), ''[[Immadi Pulikeshi (film)|Immadi Pulikeshi]]'' (1967), ''[[Sri Krishnadevaraya (film)|Sri Krishnadevaraya]]'' (1970), ''[[Bhakta Kumbara]]'' (1974), ''[[Mayura (film)|Mayura]]'' (1975), ''[[Babruvahana (film)|Babruvahana]]'' (1977) and ''[[Bhakta Prahlada (1983 film)|Bhakta Prahlada]]'' (1983). His wife [[Parvathamma Rajkumar]] founded Film production and distribution company, Vajreshwari Combines.<ref name=\"Rajakumar, king of Kannada cinema\"/>\n\nMethod actor [[Shankar Nag]] received the inaugural [[IFFI Best Actor Award (Male)]]: Silver Peacock Award\" at the [[7th International Film Festival of India]] for his work in the film ''[[Ondanondu Kaladalli]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EKo-DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT157&lpg=PT157&dq=iffi+girish+karnad+1979&source=bl&ots=i-oQyInjhS&sig=ouE2Erj4qaPNVQsqJMuI8UEP7Mc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjwpca06c_YAhUjSo8KHRMmBgIQ6AEIUTAJ#v=onepage&q=iffi+girish+karnad+1979&f=false|title=Conscience of The Race|first=BIBEKANANDA|last=RAY|date=5 April 2017|publisher=Publications Division Ministry of Information & Broadcasting|via=Google Books}}</ref> He is the younger brother of actor [[Anant Nag]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-14/news-interviews/37712791_1_shankar-nag-documentary-auto-raja|title=This one's for Shankar Nag - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YbG4HPNDlsk|title=Shankar Nag Last Interview - Part 2|first=|last=Anand Chandrashekar|date=7 November 2009|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> [[M. V. Vasudeva Rao]] was starred in over 200 films in his career; however, post ''[[Chomana Dudi]]'', he only played minor roles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rao|first1=M. K. Bhaskar|title=A natural|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/apr13/at3.htm|website=Deccan Herald|accessdate=2 May 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020425090527/http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/apr13/at3.htm|archivedate=25 April 2002|date=14 April 2002}}</ref>\n\n[[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] entered Kannada cinema with the National Award-winning movie ''[[Vamshavruksha]]'' (1972) directed by [[Girish Karnad]] based on the novel written by [[S. L. Bhyrappa]]. His first lead role was in ''[[Naagarahaavu]]'', directed by [[Puttanna Kanagal]] and based on a novel by [[T. R. Subba Rao]]. It was the first in Kannada film history to complete 100 days in three main theatres of Bangalore. In his 37-year career, he has played a variety of roles in more than 200 films.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishnuvardhan-helped-me-to-get-stardom-rajinikanth/article76796.ece | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Vishnuvardhan helped me to get stardom: Rajinikanth | date=7 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nWith his debut in [[Puttanna Kanagal]]'s National Award-winning Kannada film ''[[Naagarahaavu]]'' (1972), [[Ambareesh]]'s acting career commenced with a brief phase of portraying antagonistic and supporting characters. After establishing himself as a lead actor portraying rebellious characters on screen in a number of commercially successful films, he earned the moniker \"rebel star\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/174720/when-rebel-star-rewinds-past.html|title=When 'Rebel Star' rewinds past days in Mysore|newspaper=Deccan Herald|date=20 September 2014}}</ref> He also earned the nickname ''Mandyada Gandu'' (English: Man of [[Mandya]])<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/mandyada-gandu-gets-rousing-welcome/article5907186.ece|title=\u2018Mandyada Gandu\u2019 gets rousing welcome|newspaper=The Hindu|date=13 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[B. Saroja Devi]] is One of the most successful female leads in the history of Indian cinema, she acted in around 200 films in over six decades.<ref>[http://www.chitramala.com/articles/saroja-devi-4189.html Documentary on legendary Saroja Devi - Chitramala.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711020420/http://www.chitramala.com/articles/saroja-devi-4189.html |date=11 July 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"ToI_greatest_2013\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/B-Saroja-Devi-in-the-list-of-greatest-Indianactresses-ever/articleshow/19895895.cms |title=B Saroja Devi in the list of greatest Indian actresses ever |author=Taniya Talukdar |date=5 May 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India }}</ref> She is known by the epithets \"''Abinaya Saraswathi''\" ([[Saraswati|Saraswathi]] of acting) in Kannada and \"''Kannadathu Paingili''\" (Kannada's Parrot) in Tamil.<ref name=\"ToI_greatest_2013\"/>\n\n==Neo-realistic Cinema==\n{{main|Parallel cinema}}\nKannada Cinema majorly contributed to the [[Parallel cinema]] movement of India.<ref name=\"Kasaravalli\">{{cite|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/parallel-cinema-girish-kasaravalli-look-kannada-industrys-stalwart-filmmaker-72172|title=The parallel cinema of Girish Kasaravalli: A look at Kannada industry's stalwart filmmaker|date=2017-11-07|work=The News Minute}}</ref> Directors like [[Girish Kasaravalli]],<ref name=\"Kasaravalli\"/> [[Girish Karnad]],<ref name=\"Karnad\">{{cite|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/kannadas-parallel-cinema-loses-its-star/article26662943.ece|title=Kannada's parallel cinema loses its star|date=2019-03-28|work=The Hindu}}</ref> [[G. V. Iyer]]<ref name=\"Karnad\"/> were the early names to join the movement. [[T. S. Nagabharana]]<ref>{{cite book |date=2003 |title=Cinema in India, Volume 3 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WQtlAAAAMAAJ&q=Puttanna+Kanagal&dq=Puttanna+Kanagal&hl=en&sa=X&ei=uqSgVfWxG5PSoATz-p6QBg&ved=0CDoQ6AEwBzge |publisher=Mangala Chandran |access-date=July 11, 2015}}</ref> and [[BV Karanth]] were also popular names in the movement. [[Puttanna Kanagal]]'s films were however considered as a bridge between the Mainstream and the Parallel Cinema.\n\n==Modern Era==\n[[Prakash Raj]] began his acting career with [[Doordarshan]] serials such as ''Bisilu Kudure'' (Kannada) and ''[[Guddada Bhootha]]'' ([[Tulu language|Tulu]] and Kannada).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/if-artistes-become-cowards-they-make-society-a-coward-prakash-raj-4975924/lite|title=If artistes become cowards, they make society a coward: Prakash Raj}}</ref> He later took up supporting roles in [[Kannada language|Kannada]] films such as ''Ramachari'', ''[[Ranadheera]]'', ''[[Nishkarsha]]'' and ''[[Lockup Death]]''. He was noticed for his dialogue delivery and histrionics. His breakthrough role came in ''[[Harakeya Kuri]]'', directed by [[K. S. L. Swamy]] starring Vishnuvardhan, with whom he had acted in other films such as ''[[Mithileya Seetheyaru]]'', ''[[Muthina Haara]]'' and ''[[Nishkarsha]]''. Prakash re-entered Kannada films through ''[[Nagamandala]]'' in 1997, directed by [[T. S. Nagabharana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/india/prakash-raj-exclusive-everyone-has-the-right-to-differ-but-this-is-orchestrated-trolling-and-you-cannot-threaten-me-with-continuous-abuse-4174937.html/amp|title=Prakash Raj exclusive: Everyone has the right to differ, but this is orchestrated trolling. And you cannot threaten me with continuous abuse}}</ref> Veteran Kannada actor [[Shakti Prasad]]'s son [[Arjun Sarja]] is known for his works in South Indian cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/41510/sandalwood/four-films-announced-for-23rd-march-news-details |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320165539/http://www.supergoodmovies.com/41510/sandalwood/four-films-announced-for-23rd-march-news-details |archivedate=20 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was starred in works such as [[Prasad (2012 film)|Prasad]], the film was screened at the [[Berlin Film Festival]], and Arjun received the Karnataka State Award for his performance.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-23/news-interviews/31090458_1_martin-gropius-bau-festival-director-indian-film]</ref>\n\n[[Sanchari Vijay]]'s portrayal of a transgender won him the [[National Film Award for Best Actor|National Best Actor Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vijay bags National Award for Best Actor|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Vijay-bags-National-Award-for-Best-Actor/articleshow/46676471.cms|publisher=timesofindia|date=24 March 2015|accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sanchari Vijay Actor\u2013Profile and biography|url=http://cinetrooth.in/2015/06/21/sanchari-vijay-actor-profile-and-biography/|publisher=cinetrooth|date=21 June 2015|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Vijay elated on winning best actor award|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/467499/vijay-elated-winning-actor-award.html|publisher=deccanherald|date=25 March 2015|accessdate=2015-03-26}}</ref> With the award win, Vijay became the third actor after [[M. V. Vasudeva Rao]], and [[Charuhasan]] to win the National Award for Best Actor for performing in a [[Kannada film]].<ref>http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/meet-the-first-kannada-actor-to-win-a-national-award-south/20150325.htm</ref>\n\n[[Shiva Rajkumar]] is known for his work in ''[[Janumada Jodi]]'', ''[[Anand (1986 film)|Anand]]'', ''[[Ratha Sapthami]]'', ''[[Nammoora Mandara Hoove]]'', ''[[Om]]'' ''[[Simhada Mari]]'', and ''[[Chigurida Kanasu]]''. He acted in ''[[Sugreeva (film)|Sugreeva]]'', which was shot in 18 hours. His ''[[Om (Kannada film)|Om]]'', directed by [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]], set a trend of gangster movies in [[Kannada]] and other film industries in India. It continues to be shown even to this day.<ref>[http://kannada.oneindia.in/movies/news/2010/09/01-upendra-om-re-release-on-sept-3.html \u0caa\u0ccd\u0cb0\u0cc7\u0c95\u0ccd\u0cb7\u0c95\u0cb0 \u0c92\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cbe\u0caf\u0ca6 \u0cae\u0cc7\u0cb0\u0cc6\u0c97\u0cc6 \u0cae\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cc6 \u0cac\u0c82\u0ca6\u0cbf\u0ca6\u0cc6 \u0c93\u0c82!], One India, 1 September 2010</ref>\n\n[[Rockline Venkatesh]] founded [[Rockline Entertainments]] which has produced over twenty five films as of 2012.<ref name=\"63rdaward\">{{cite press_release|title=63rd National Film Awards|url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf|format=PDF|publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]]|date=28 March 2016|accessdate=28 March 2016}}</ref> New age actors [[Puneeth Rajkumar]], [[Rakshith Shetty]], and [[Yash (actor)|Yash]] are one of the highest-paid actors in Sandalwood.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-pk-mr-mrs-ramachari-dominate-bengaluru-collection-centres-619818 Box Office Collection: 'PK', 'Mr & Mrs Ramachari' Dominate Bengaluru Collection Centres]. Ibtimes.co.in (9 January 2015). Retrieved on 11 November 2016.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/birthday-gift-to-yash-ramachari-to-enter-20-cr-club-soon-news-kannada-pbikMujcjecag.html|title=Birthday gift to Yash: Ramachari to enter cr club soon!|agency=www.sify.com|access-date=22 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822145507/https://www.sify.com/movies/birthday-gift-to-yash-ramachari-to-enter-20-cr-club-soon-news-kannada-pbikMujcjecag.html|archive-date=22 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= 'Mr and Mrs Ramachari' Review: Audience Live Response |url= http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mr-mrs-ramachari-review-audience-live-response-618291 |publisher= ibtimes.co.in |date= 25 December 2014 |accessdate= 2 January 2015}}</ref> The [[Rakshith Shetty]] starrer ''[[Kirik Party]]'' opened to {{cn span|widespread acclaim from critics and audiences alike|date=January 2020}} and went on to become the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing film]] of the year by collecting \u20b950 [[crore]]<ref name=\"ittt\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party dubbed by malayalam movie premam and Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|publisher=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> against production budget \u20b94 crore,<ref name=\"th\">{{cite web|title=The budget of \u2018Kirik Party\u2019 would be around \u20b94crore|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/rakshith-shettys-kirik-party-to-go-on-the-floors-in-march/article8191273.ece\n|work=The Hindu}}</ref> and completed 150-days in main centers of [[Karnataka]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/krik-party-rakshit-shetty-rashmika-mandanna-celebrate-150-days-981176-2017-06-06|title=Kirik Party completes 150 days: Rakshit Shetty, Rashmika Mandanna celebrate with fans|website=India Today}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, [[K.G.F: Chapter 1]] became the first [[Kannada]] film to gross \u20b9100 crores, \u20b9200 crores and \u20b9250 crores at the box office. A sequel is slated to release on 23rd October 2020.<ref> https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/yash-reveals-he-has-approached-sanjay-dutt-for-kgf-chapter-2-1452187-2019-02-09</ref>\n\n==Film Score==\nComposer [[Hamsalekha]] is usually referred to by the title ''Naadha Brahma'' (English: The [[Brahma]] of Music) who is considered to be the major cause for the change in the music composing and lyric writing style which would appeal much to the younger generation. He integrated folk and introduced western musical sensibilities into the Kannada cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chitraloka.com/news/1472-hamsalekha-60.html|title=Hamsalekha 60|publisher=Chitraloka|date=23 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/dr-hamsalekha-now-kannada-news-107448|title=Dr. Hamsalekha now|publisher=Indiaglitz|date=14 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[Mano Murthy]] scored the blockbuster film [[Mungaru Male]] starring [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]] and [[Pooja Gandhi]]. Upon the album's release, it topped the charts with the song \"[[Anisuthide]]\" receiving significant radio and TV air time.<ref name = hindu>{{cite news |title='Mungaru Male' still tops the charts |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/mungaru-male-still-tops-the-charts/article1843484.ece |newspaper=The Hindu |date=17 May 2014 |accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> The album emerged as a massive success topping every Kannada music chart. It was reported that by mid-May 2007, over 200,000 copies were sold in [[compact disc]]s.<ref>{{cite news |title='Mungaru Male' album a mega hit |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1273374021.html |accessdate=10 October 2015 |work=Hindustan Times |date=18 May 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151010052639/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1273374021.html |archivedate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Film Schools==\nThe first government institute in India to start technical courses related to films was established in 1941 named as occupational institute then called the Sri Jayachamarajendra (S J) Polytechnic in [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]]. In September 1996, two specialized courses, Cinematography and Sound & Television were separated and the [[Government Film and Television Institute]] was started at [[Hesaraghatta]], under the World Bank Assisted Project for Technician Development in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=GFTI|url=http://www.filminstitutebangalore.com/index.htm|website=www.filminstitutebangalore.com|accessdate=22 August 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140821235404/http://www.filminstitutebangalore.com/index.htm|archivedate=21 August 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==State Awards==\n[[File:Karnataka Chalanachitra Kalavidara Sangha-img.jpg|thumb|150px|right|Karnataka Chalanachitra Kalavidara Sangha in [[Chamrajpet|Chamrajapet]]]]\n* [[Karnataka State Film Awards]]\n* [[Udaya Film Awards]]\n* [[Suvarna Film Awards]]\n\n==State Festivals==\n* [[Bangalore International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biffes.in/|title=Bengaluru International Film Festival - BIFFES|work=Bengaluru International Film Festival}}</ref>\n\n==Other Awards==\n* [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n* [[SIIMA Awards]]\n* [[IIFA Utsavam]]\n* [[Mirchi Music Awards South]]\n* [[South Scope|South Scope Awards]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Kannada-language films]]\n* [[Media in Karnataka]]\n* [[Cinema of India]]\n* [[Media of India]]\n* [[List of Kannada film actresses]]\n\n==Highest-grossing Kannada films by year==\n{| style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Film\n! Year\n! Director(s